msgstr "在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到您的 {rhel}{nbsp}9 CLM 项目。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle-examples.adoc:154
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Matcher`` field, select [parameter]``none (disable "
"modularity)``."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``匹配器``字段中选择[parameter]``无（禁用模块化）``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle-examples.adoc:158
msgid ""
"This will effectively remove the module metadata from the target repository, "
"excluding any package that belongs to a module."
msgstr "这样会有效从目标储存库中去除模块元数据，并排除属于模块的所有软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle-examples.adoc:159
msgid ""
"When you build your CLM project using the btn:[Build] button in the {webui}, "
"the target repository is a regular repository without any modules, that "
"contains packages from the selected module streams."
msgstr ""
"当您使用 {webui} 中的 btn:[构建] 按钮构建 CLM 项目时，目标储存库是不包含任何"
"模块的常规储存库，其中包含来自选定模块流的软件包。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle-examples.adoc:160
msgid ""
"Disabling modularity altogether in {rhel}{nbsp}8 projects might result in a "
"faulty environment as some modules are essential for healthy operation in "
"{rhel}{nbsp}8."
msgstr ""
"在 {rhel}{nbsp}8 项目中完全禁用模块化可能导致环境存在缺陷，因为在 {rhel}"
"{nbsp}8 中，某些模块对于系统的健康运行是不可或缺的。"

#.  This feature is mandatory to make RHEL/CentOS 8 modular repositories work
#.  in the SUMA UI. Otherwise, even though modular repositories can be synced
#.  and assigned to clients, they cannot be used for package operations
#.  (install, update, etc.) from SUMA UI (An info message is shown in the UI if
#.  that's the case). In that case, the package operations can only be done
#.  from the client's CLI manually.
#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Content Lifecycle Management"
msgstr "内容生命周期管理"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Content lifecycle management allows you to customize and test packages "
"before updating production clients.  This is especially useful if you need "
"to apply updates during a limited maintenance window."
msgstr ""
"内容生命周期管理允许您在更新生产客户端之前自定义和测试软件包。如果您需要在有"
"限的维护时段内应用更新，此功能将特别有用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:3
msgid ""
"Content lifecycle management allows you to select software channels as "
"sources, adjust them as required for your environment, and thoroughly test "
"them before installing onto your production clients."
msgstr ""
"内容生命周期管理允许您选择软件通道作为源、根据环境的需要调整软件通道，并在安"
"装到生产客户端之前对其进行全面的测试。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:4
msgid ""
"While you cannot directly modify vendor channels, you can clone them and "
"then modify the clones by adding or removing packages and custom patches.  "
"You can assign these cloned channels to test clients to ensure they work as "
"expected.  Then, when all tests pass, you can promote them to production "
"servers."
msgstr ""
"虽然您无法直接修改供应商通道，但可以克隆它们，然后通过添加或去除软件包和自定"
"义补丁来修改克隆版本。可以将这些克隆的通道指派到测试客户端，以确保它们按预期"
"工作。然后，在所有测试通过后，可以将它们升级到生产服务器。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:5
msgid ""
"This is achieved through a series of environments that your software "
"channels can move through on their lifecycle.  Most environment lifecycles "
"include at least test and production environments, but you can have as many "
"environments as you require."
msgstr ""
"此功能是通过一系列环境实现的，软件通道在其生命周期内可以在这些环境之间转移。"
"大多数环境生命周期至少包括测试和生产环境，但您可以创建任意所需数量的环境。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:6
msgid ""
"This section covers the basic content lifecycle procedures, and the filters "
"available.  For more specific examples, see xref:administration:content-"
"lifecycle-examples.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"本章介绍基本的内容生命周期过程以及可用的过滤器。有关更具体的示例，请参见 "
"xref:administration:content-lifecycle-examples.adoc[]。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create a Content Lifecycle Project"
msgstr "创建内容生命周期项目"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:8
msgid ""
"To set up a content lifecycle, you need to begin with a project.  The "
"project defines the software channel sources, the filters used to find "
"packages, and the build environments."
msgstr ""
"要设置内容生命周期，需要从一个项目开始。该项目定义软件通道源、用于查找软件包"
"的过滤器，以及构建环境。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Creating a Content Lifecycle Project"
msgstr "过程：创建内容生命周期项目"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:10
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Content Lifecycle[Projects], "
"and click btn:[Create Project]."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:内容生命周期[项目]并单击 btn:[创建项"
"目]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:11
msgid "In the [guimenu]``Label`` field, enter a label for your project."
msgstr "在 [guimenu]``标签``字段中输入项目的标签。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:12
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:25
msgid ""
"The [guimenu]``Label`` field only accepts lowercase letters, numbers, "
"periods, hyphens, and underscores."
msgstr "[guimenu]``标签``字段仅接受小写字母、数字、句点、连字符和下划线。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:13
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Name`` field, enter a descriptive name for your project."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``名称``字段中输入项目的描述性名称。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Click the btn:[Create] button to create your project and return to the "
"project page."
msgstr "单击 btn:[创建] 按钮以创建项目并返回项目页面。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:15
msgid "Click btn:[Attach/Detach Sources]."
msgstr "单击 btn:[挂接/分离源]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:16
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Sources`` dialog, select the source type, and select a "
"base channel for your project."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``源``对话框中选择源类型，然后选择项目的基础通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:17
msgid ""
"The available child channels for the selected base channel are displayed, "
"including information on whether the channel is mandatory or recommended."
msgstr ""
"此时会显示所选基础通道的可用子通道，包括有关通道是必需通道还是建议通道的信"
"息。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Check the child channels you require, and click btn:[Save] to return to the "
"project page."
msgstr "选中所需的子通道，然后单击 btn:[保存] 返回项目页面。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:19
msgid "The software channels you selected should now be showing."
msgstr "您选择的软件通道现在应会显示出来。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:21
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Filters`` dialog, select the filters you want to attach to "
"the project."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``筛选器``对话框中，选择要挂接到项目的过滤器。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:22
msgid "To create a new filter, click btn:[Create new Filter]."
msgstr "要创建新过滤器，请单击 btn:[创建新过滤器]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:23
msgid "Click btn:[Add Environment]."
msgstr "单击 btn:[添加环境]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:24
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Environment Lifecycle`` dialog, give the first environment "
"a name, a label, and a description, and click btn:[Save]."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``环境生命周期``对话框中，为第一个环境指定名称、标签和说明，然后单"
"击 btn:[保存]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:26
msgid ""
"Continue creating environments until you have all the environments for your "
"lifecycle completed."
msgstr "继续创建环境，直到为整个生命周期创建了所有环境。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:27
msgid ""
"You can select the order of the environments in the lifecycle by selecting "
"an environment in the [guimenu]``Insert before`` field when you create it."
msgstr ""
"可以选择环境在生命周期中的顺序，方法是在创建某个环境时在[guimenu]``在前面插入"
"``字段中选择该环境。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filter Types"
msgstr "过滤器类型"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:29
msgid ""
"{productname} allows you to create various types of filters to control the "
"content used for building the project.  Filters allow you to select which "
"packages are included or excluded from the build.  For example, you could "
"exclude all kernel packages, or include only specific releases of some "
"packages."
msgstr ""
"{productname} 允许您创建各种类型的过滤器来控制用于构建项目的内容。使用过滤器"
"可以选择要在构建中包含或排除哪些软件包。例如，可以排除所有内核软件包，或仅包"
"含某些软件包的特定发行版。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:30
msgid "The supported filters are:"
msgstr "支持的过滤器为："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:31
msgid "package filtering"
msgstr "软件包过滤"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:32
msgid "by name"
msgstr "按名称"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:33
msgid "by name, epoch, version, release, and architecture"
msgstr "按名称、纪元、版本、发行版和体系结构"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:34
msgid "by provided name"
msgstr "按提供的名称"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:35
msgid "patch filtering"
msgstr "补丁过滤"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:36
msgid "by advisory name"
msgstr "按建议名称"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:37
msgid "by advisory type"
msgstr "按建议类型"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:38
msgid "by synopsis"
msgstr "按摘要"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:39
msgid "by keyword"
msgstr "按关键字"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:40
msgid "by date"
msgstr "按日期"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:41
msgid "by affected package"
msgstr "按受影响的软件包"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:42
msgid "module"
msgstr "模块"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:43
msgid "by stream"
msgstr "按流"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:44
msgid "Package dependencies are not resolved during content filtering."
msgstr "在内容过滤期间不会解析软件包依赖项。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:45
msgid ""
"There are multiple matchers you can use with the filter.  Which ones are "
"available depends on the filter type you choose."
msgstr ""
"可以将多个匹配器与过滤器配合使用。哪些匹配器可用取决于所选的过滤器类型。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:46
msgid "The available matchers are:"
msgstr "可用的匹配器为："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:47
msgid "contains"
msgstr "包含"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:48
msgid "matches (must take the form of a regular expression)"
msgstr "匹配（必须采用正则表达式形式）"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:49
msgid "equals"
msgstr "等于"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:50
msgid "greater"
msgstr "大于"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:51
msgid "greater or equal"
msgstr "大于或等于"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:52
msgid "lower or equal"
msgstr "低于或等于"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:53
msgid "lower"
msgstr "低于"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:54
msgid "later or equal"
msgstr "高于或等于"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filter ``rule`` Parameter"
msgstr "过滤器``规则``参数"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:56
msgid ""
"Each filter has a ``rule`` parameter that can be set to either ``Allow`` or "
"``Deny``.  The filters are processed like this:"
msgstr ""
"每个过滤器都有一个``规则``参数，可将此参数设置为``允许``或``拒绝``。过滤器的"
"处理方式如下："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:57
msgid ""
"If a package or patch satisfies a ``Deny`` filter, it is excluded from the "
"result."
msgstr "如果某个软件包或补丁满足``拒绝``过滤器的条件，则从结果中排除它。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:58
msgid ""
"If a package or patch satisfies an ``Allow`` filter, it is included in the "
"result (even if it was excluded by a ``Deny`` filter)."
msgstr ""
"如果某个软件包或补丁满足``允许``过滤器的条件，则将它包含在结果中（即使它已由"
"``拒绝``过滤器排除）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:59
msgid ""
"This behavior is useful when you want to exclude large number of packages or "
"patches using a general ``Deny`` filter and \"cherry-pick\" specific "
"packages or patches with specific ``Allow`` filters."
msgstr ""
"当您想要使用一般的``拒绝``过滤器来排除大量软件包或补丁，并想要使用特定的``允"
"许``过滤器来“挑选”特定的软件包或补丁时，此行为很有用。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:60
msgid ""
"Content filters are global in your organization and can be shared between "
"projects."
msgstr "内容过滤器在您的组织中是全局性的，并可以在项目之间共享。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:61
msgid ""
"If your project already contains built sources, when you add an environment "
"it is automatically populated with the existing content.  Content is drawn "
"from the previous environment of the cycle if it had one.  If there is no "
"previous environment, it is left empty until the project sources are built "
"again."
msgstr ""
"如果您的项目已包含构建的源，当您添加环境时，该环境中会自动填充现有内容。内容"
"是从周期中的前一个环境（如果有）提取的。如果前一个环境不存在，则将内容留空，"
"直到再次构建了项目源。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "Filter Templates"
msgstr "过滤器模板"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:63
msgid ""
"To help with creating filters for some common scenarios, {productname} "
"offers filter templates.  When applied, these templates help creating a set "
"of filters in advance, tailored for a specific use case."
msgstr ""
"为了帮助为某些常见方案创建过滤器，{productname} 提供了过滤器模板。应用这些模"
"板有助于提前创建一组针对特定用例定制的过滤器。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:64
msgid "This section describes available templates and their usages."
msgstr "本节介绍可用的模板及其用法。"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "Live patching based on a SUSE product"
msgstr "根据 SUSE 产品在线增补"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:66
msgid ""
"In a project that contains live patching, regular future kernel packages "
"must be excluded so that only live patch packages are offered as updates to "
"clients. On the other hand, already installed regular kernel packages must "
"still be included to keep system integrity."
msgstr ""
"在包含在线增补的项目中，必须排除未来的常规内核软件包，以便仅将在线补丁软件包"
"作为更新提供给客户端。另一方面，仍然必须包含已安装的常规内核软件包以保持系统"
"完整性。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:67
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:85
msgid ""
"When applied, this template creates three filters required to achieve this "
"behavior:"
msgstr "应用此模板会创建三个所需的过滤器来实现以下行为："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:68
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:86
msgid ""
"Allow patches that contain ``kernel-default`` package equal to a base kernel "
"version"
msgstr "允许其中包含与基础内核版本相同的 ``kernel-default`` 软件包的补丁"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:69
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:87
msgid "Deny patches that contain ``reboot_suggested`` keyword"
msgstr "拒绝其中包含 ``reboot_suggested`` 关键字的补丁"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:70
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:88
msgid ""
"Deny patches that contain a package which provides the name "
"``installhint(reboot-needed)``"
msgstr "拒绝其中包含带有名称 ``installhint(reboot-needed)`` 的软件包的补丁"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:71
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:89
msgid ""
"For more information on how to set up a live patching project, see xref:"
"administration:content-lifecycle-examples.adoc#exclude-higher-kernel-"
"version[]."
msgstr ""
"有关如何设置在线增补项目的详细信息，请参见 xref:administration:content-"
"lifecycle-examples.adoc#exclude-higher-kernel-version[]。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:72
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:90
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:109
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Applying the template"
msgstr "过程：应用模板"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:74
msgid ""
"In the dialog, click btn:[Use a template]. The inputs will change "
"accordingly."
msgstr "在对话框中单击 btn:[使用模板]。输入将相应地更改。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:75
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Prefix`` field, type a name prefix. This value will be "
"prepended to the name of every individual filter created by the template. If "
"the template is being applied in the context of a project, this field will "
"be prefilled with the project label."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``前缀``字段中键入名称前缀。此值将添加到模板创建的每个过滤器的名称"
"前面。如果在项目上下文中应用模板，则此字段中会预先填充项目标签。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:76
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Template`` field, select [guimenu]``Live patching based on "
"a SUSE product``."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``模板``字段中，选择[guimenu]``根据 SUSE 产品在线增补``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:77
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Product`` field, select the product you wish to set up "
"live patching for."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``产品``字段中，选择要为其设置在线增补的产品。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:78
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Kernel`` field, select a kernel version from the list of "
"versions available in the selected product. The filter to deny the later "
"regular kernel patches will be based on this version."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``内核``字段中，从所选产品的可用版本列表中选择一个内核版本。拒绝后"
"续常规内核补丁的过滤器将基于此版本。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:79
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:97
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:116
msgid "Click btn:[Save] to create the filters."
msgstr "单击 btn:[保存] 以创建过滤器。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:82
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:100
msgid ""
"Select the three filters that have the specified prefix, and click btn:"
"[Save]."
msgstr "选择具有指定前缀的三个过滤器，然后单击 btn:[保存]。"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Live patching based on a system"
msgstr "根据系统在线增补"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:84
msgid ""
"When you want to set up a live patching project based on a kernel version "
"installed in a specific registered system, you can use the \"live patching "
"based on a system\" template."
msgstr ""
"如果您想要根据特定已注册系统中安装的内核版本设置在线增补项目，可以使用``根据"
"系统在线增补``模板。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:92
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:112
msgid ""
"In the dialog, click btn:[Use a template].  The inputs will change "
"accordingly."
msgstr "在对话框中单击 btn:[使用模板]。输入将相应地更改。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:93
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:113
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Prefix`` field, type a name prefix.  This value will be "
"prepended to the name of every filter created by the template.  If the "
"template is being applied in the context of a project, this field will be "
"prefilled with the project label."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``前缀``字段中键入名称前缀。此值将添加到模板创建的每个过滤器的名称"
"前面。如果在项目上下文中应用模板，则此字段中会预先填充项目标签。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:94
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Template`` field, select [guimenu]``Live patching based on "
"a specific system``."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``模板``字段中，选择[guimenu]``根据特定系统在线增补``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:95
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``System`` field, select a system from the list, or start "
"typing a system name to narrow down the options."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``系统``字段中，从列表中选择一个系统，或键入系统名称以缩小选项的范"
"围。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:96
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Kernel`` field, select a kernel version from the list of "
"versions installed in the selected system.  The filter to deny the later "
"regular kernel patches will be based on this version."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``内核``字段中，从所选系统上安装的版本列表中选择一个内核版本。拒绝"
"后续常规内核补丁的过滤器将基于此版本。"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "AppStream modules with defaults"
msgstr "含默认值的 AppStream 模块"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:102
msgid ""
"When you want to have all the modules available in a modular repository "
"included in your project, you can automatically add them using this filter "
"template."
msgstr ""
"如果您想要在项目中包含模块化储存库中提供的所有可用模块，可以使用此过滤器模板"
"自动添加这些模块。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:103
msgid ""
"When applied, this template creates an AppStream filter per module and its "
"default stream."
msgstr "应用后，此模板将为每个模块及其默认流创建一个 AppStream 过滤器。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:104
msgid ""
"If this process is done from the project's page, the filters are added to "
"the project automatically. Otherwise, the created filters can be listed in "
"menu:Content Lifecycle[Filters] and be added to any project as needed."
msgstr ""
"如果从项目的页面完成此过程，则过滤器将自动添加到项目。否则，创建的过滤器可能"
"会列在menu:内容生命周期[过滤器]中，并根据需要添加到任何项目。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:105
msgid ""
"Each individual filter can be edited to select a different module stream, or "
"removed altogether to exclude that module from the target repositories."
msgstr ""
"可以编辑每个过滤器以选择不同的模块流，或去除所有这些过滤器以从目标储存库中排"
"除该模块。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:106
msgid ""
"Because not all module streams are compatible with each other, changing "
"individual streams may prevent successful resolution of modular "
"dependencies. When this happens, the filters pane in the project details "
"page will show an error describing the problem, and the build button will be "
"disabled until all the module selections are compatible."
msgstr ""
"由于并非所有模块流都相互兼容，因此更改单个流可能会导致无法成功解析模块化依赖"
"关系。如果发生这种情况，项目细节页面中的过滤器窗格会显示描述问题的错误，并且"
"在选择的所有模块都兼容之前，构建按钮将会禁用。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:107
msgid ""
"Since {rhel}{nbsp}9, modules do not have any defined default streams.  "
"Therefore, using this template with {rhel}{nbsp}9 sources will have no "
"effect."
msgstr ""
"自 {rhel}{nbsp}9 起，模块便不再具有任何定义的默认流。因此，对 {rhel}{nbsp}9 "
"源使用此模板将不会有任何效果。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:108
msgid ""
"For more information on how to set up AppStream repositories with content "
"lifecycle management, see xref:administration:content-lifecycle-examples."
"adoc#appstream-filters[]."
msgstr ""
"有关如何使用内容生命周期管理设置 AppStream 储存库的详细信息，请参见 xref:"
"administration:content-lifecycle-examples.adoc#appstream-filters[]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:110
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Content Lifecycle[Projects], "
"and select your project."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:内容生命周期[项目]，然后选择您的项"
"目。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:111
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Filters`` section, click btn:[Attach/Detach Filters], and "
"then click btn:[Create New Filter]."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``过滤器``部分，单击 btn:[挂接/分离过滤器]，然后单击 btn:[创建新过"
"滤器]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:114
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Template`` field, select [guimenu]``AppStream modules with "
"defaults``."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``模板``字段中，选择[guimenu]``含默认值的 AppStream 模块``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:115
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Channel`` field, select a modular channel to get the "
"modules from. In this dropdown, only the modular channels are displayed."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``通道``字段中，选择一个模块化通道以从中获取模块。此下拉列表中仅显"
"示模块化通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:117
msgid ""
"Scroll to the [guimenu]``Filters`` section to see the newly attached "
"AppStream filters."
msgstr "滚动到[guimenu]``过滤器``部分以查看新挂接的 AppStream 过滤器。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:118
msgid ""
"You can edit/remove any individual filter to tailor the project to your "
"needs."
msgstr "可以编辑/去除任何一个过滤器以根据您的需要定制项目。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Build a Content Lifecycle Project"
msgstr "构建内容生命周期项目"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:120
msgid ""
"When you have created your project, defined environments, and attached "
"sources and filters, you can build the project for the first time."
msgstr "创建项目、定义环境、挂接源和过滤器后，可以首次构建项目。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:121
msgid ""
"Building applies filters to the attached sources and clones them to the "
"first environment in the project."
msgstr "构建过程会将过滤器应用于挂接的源，并将过滤器克隆到项目中的第一个环境。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:122
msgid ""
"You can use the same vendor channels as sources for multiple content "
"projects.  In this case, {productname} does not create new patch clones for "
"each cloned channel.  Instead, a single patch clone is shared between all of "
"your cloned channels.  This can cause problems if a vendor modifies a patch; "
"for example, if the patch is retracted, or the packages within the patch are "
"changed.  When you build one of the content projects, all the channels that "
"share the cloned patch are synchronized with the original by default, even "
"if the channels are in other environments of your content project, or other "
"content project channels in your organization.  You can change this behavior "
"by turning off automatic patch synchronization in your organization "
"settings.  To manually synchronize the patch later for all channels sharing "
"the patch, navigate to menu:Software[Manage > Channels], click the channel "
"you want to synchronize and navigate to the [guimenu]``Sync`` subtab.  Even "
"manual patch synchronization affects all organization channels sharing the "
"patch."
msgstr ""
"可以使用相同的供应商通道作为多个内容项目的源。在这种情况下，{productname} 不"
"会为每个克隆的通道创建新的补丁克隆版本，而是在所有克隆的通道之间共享一个补丁"
"克隆版本。如果供应商修改了某个补丁（例如，撤回了该补丁，或者更改了补丁中的软"
"件包），则这可能会导致问题。当您构建某个内容项目时，默认情况下，共享克隆补丁"
"的所有通道将与原始通道同步，即使这些共享通道位于内容项目的其他环境中，或者位"
"于您的组织的其他内容项目通道中，也是如此。可以通过在组织设置中关闭自动补丁同"
"步来更改此行为。要在以后为共享补丁的所有通道手动同步补丁，请导航到menu:软件"
"[管理 > 通道]，单击要同步的通道，然后导航到[guimenu]``同步``子选项卡。即使手"
"动同步补丁，也会影响共享补丁的所有组织通道。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Building a Content Lifecycle Project"
msgstr "过程：构建内容生命周期项目"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:124
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Content Lifecycle[Projects], "
"and select the project you want to build."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:内容生命周期[项目]，然后选择您要构建"
"的项目。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:125
msgid ""
"Make sure you have the environment available before building the project."
msgstr "在构建项目前，请确保环境可用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:126
msgid "Review the attached sources and filters, and click btn:[Build]."
msgstr "查看挂接的源和过滤器，然后单击 btn:[构建]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:127
msgid ""
"Provide a version message to describe the changes or updates in this build."
msgstr "提供版本消息以描述此构建中的更改或更新。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:128
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:135
msgid ""
"You can monitor build progress in the [guimenu]``Environment Lifecycle`` "
"section."
msgstr "可以在[guimenu]``环境生命周期``部分监视构建进度。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:129
msgid ""
"After the build is finished, the environment version is increased by one and "
"the built sources, such as software channels, can be assigned to your "
"clients."
msgstr ""
"构建完成后，环境版本号将会加 1，可将构建的源（例如软件通道）指派到您的客户"
"端。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:130
#, no-wrap
msgid "Promote Environments"
msgstr "升级环境"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:131
msgid ""
"When the project has been built, the built sources can be sequentially "
"promoted to the environments."
msgstr "构建项目后，可将构建的源按顺序升级到环境。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:132
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Promoting Environments"
msgstr "过程：升级环境"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:133
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Content Lifecycle[Projects], "
"and select the project you want to work with."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:内容生命周期[项目]，然后选择您要处理"
"的项目。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:134
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Environment Lifecycle`` section, locate the environment to "
"promote to its successor, and click btn:[Promote]."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``环境生命周期``部分，找到要升级到其后继版本的环境，然后单击 btn:"
"[升级]。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assign Clients to Environments"
msgstr "将客户端指派到环境"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:137
msgid ""
"When you build and promote content lifecycle projects, {productname} creates "
"a tree of software channels.  To add clients to the environment, assign the "
"base and child software channels to your client using menu:Software[Software "
"Channels] in the [guimenu]``System Details`` page for the client."
msgstr ""
"当您构建和升级内容生命周期项目时，{productname} 会创建一个软件通道树。要将客"
"户端添加到环境，请使用客户端的[guimenu]``系统细节``页面中的menu:软件[软件通"
"道]将基础通道和子软件通道指派到客户端。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:138
msgid ""
"Newly added cloned channels are not assigned to clients automatically.  If "
"you add or promote sources you need to manually check and update your "
"channel assignments."
msgstr ""
"新添加的克隆通道不会自动指派到客户端。如果您添加或升级了源，则需要手动检查并"
"更新您的通道指派。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-lifecycle.adoc:139
msgid ""
"Automatic assignment is intended to be added to {productname} in a future "
"version."
msgstr "在将来的版本中，自动指派会添加到 {productname}。"

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Content Staging"
msgstr "内容暂存"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Staging is used by clients to download packages in advance, before they are "
"installed.  This allows package installation to begin as soon as it is "
"scheduled, which can reduce the amount of time required for a maintenance "
"window."
msgstr ""
"客户端使用暂存来预先下载软件包，然后再安装软件包。这样就可以在做好安排后立即"
"开始安装软件包，从而减少维护时段占用的时间。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enable Content Staging"
msgstr "启用内容暂存"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:4
msgid ""
"You can manage content staging across your entire organization.  In the "
"{productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Admin[Organizations] to see a list "
"of available organizations.  Click the name of an organization, and check "
"the [guimenu]``Enable Staging Contents`` box to allow clients in this "
"organization to stage package data."
msgstr ""
"您可以管理整个组织中的内容暂存。在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:管理"
"[组织]以查看可用组织的列表。单击某个组织的名称，然后选中[guimenu]``启用暂存内"
"容``框以允许此组织中的客户端暂存软件包数据。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:5
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:6
msgid ""
"You must be logged in as the {productname} administrator to create and "
"manage organizations."
msgstr "您必须以 {productname} 管理员身份登录才能创建和管理组织。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:6
msgid ""
"You can also enable staging at the command prompt by editing [path]``/etc/"
"sysconfig/rhn/up2date``, and adding or editing these lines:"
msgstr ""
"也可以在命令提示符下通过编辑 [path]``/etc/sysconfig/rhn/up2date`` 并添加或编"
"辑下面一行内容来启用暂存："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"stagingContent=1\n"
"stagingContentWindow=24\n"
msgstr ""
"stagingContent=1\n"
"stagingContentWindow=24\n"

#. 2018-12-10, ke: /etc/sysconfig/rhn/up2date still exists. @renner confirmed some tools use it (at least, trad. client).  To be renamed in the future.
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:8
msgid ""
"The ``stagingContentWindow`` parameter is a time value expressed in hours "
"and determines when downloading starts.  It is the number of hours before "
"the scheduled installation or update time.  In this example, content is "
"downloaded 24 hours before the installation time.  The start time for "
"download depends on the selected contact method for a system.  The assigned "
"contact method sets the time for when the next [command]``mgr_check`` is "
"executed."
msgstr ""
"``stagingContentWindow`` 参数是以小时为单位的时间值，用于确定下载何时开始。它"
"是距离安排的安装或更新时间的小时数。在此示例中，将在安装时间之前的 24 小时开"
"始下载内容。下载开始时间取决于为系统选择的联系方法。指派的联系方法设置下一个 "
"[command]``mgr_check`` 的执行时间。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Next time an action is scheduled, packages are automatically downloaded, but "
"not installed.  At the scheduled time, the staged packages are installed."
msgstr ""
"下一次安排操作后，会自动下载但不安装软件包。将在安排的时间安装暂存的软件包。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure Content Staging"
msgstr "配置内容暂存"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:11
msgid "There are two parameters used to configure content staging:"
msgstr "有两个参数用于配置内容暂存："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:12
msgid ""
"[parameter]``salt_content_staging_advance`` is the advance time for the "
"content staging window to open, in hours."
msgstr ""
"[parameter]``salt_content_staging_advance`` 是内容暂存时段开始之前预先经过的"
"一段时间，以小时为单位。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:13
msgid ""
"This is the number of hours before installation starts, that package "
"downloads can begin."
msgstr "它是距离安装开始的小时数，经过这段时间后即可开始下载软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:14
msgid ""
"[parameter]``salt_content_staging_window`` is the duration of the content "
"staging window, in hours."
msgstr ""
"[parameter]``salt_content_staging_window`` 是内容暂存时段的持续时间，以小时为"
"单位。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:15
msgid ""
"This is the amount of time clients have to stage packages before "
"installation begins."
msgstr "这是在安装开始之前客户端必须将软件包暂存的一段时间。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:16
msgid ""
"For example, if [parameter]``salt_content_staging_advance`` is set to six "
"hours, and [parameter]``salt_content_staging_window`` is set to two hours, "
"the staging window opens six hours before the installation time, and remain "
"open for two hours.  No packages are downloaded in the four remaining hours "
"until installation starts."
msgstr ""
"例如，如果 [parameter]``salt_content_staging_advance`` 设置为六小时，"
"[parameter]``salt_content_staging_window`` 设置为两小时，则暂存时段在安装时间"
"到来之前的六小时开始，并持续两小时。在安装开始之前的剩余四个小时内不会下载任"
"何软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:17
msgid ""
"If you set the same value for both "
"[parameter]``salt_content_staging_advance`` and "
"[parameter]``salt_content_staging_window`` packages are able to be "
"downloaded until installation begins."
msgstr ""
"如果您为 [parameter]``salt_content_staging_advance`` 和 "
"[parameter]``salt_content_staging_window`` 设置相同的值，则可以在安装开始之前"
"下载软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Configure the content staging parameters in [path]``/usr/share/rhn/config-"
"defaults/rhn_java.conf``."
msgstr ""
"在 [path]``/usr/share/rhn/config-defaults/rhn_java.conf`` 中配置内容暂存参"
"数。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:19
msgid "Default values:"
msgstr "默认值："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:20
msgid "[path]``salt_content_staging_advance: 8 hours``"
msgstr "[path]``salt_content_staging_advance：8 小时``"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:21
msgid "[path]``salt_content_staging_window: 8 hours``"
msgstr "[path]``salt_content_staging_window：8 小时``"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/content-staging.adoc:22
msgid "Content staging must be enabled for these parameters to work correctly."
msgstr "必须启用内容暂存才能让这些参数正常工作。"

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Custom Channels"
msgstr "自定义通道"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Custom channels give you the ability to create your own software packages "
"and repositories, which you can use to update your clients.  They also allow "
"you to use software provided by third party vendors in your environment."
msgstr ""
"自定义通道使您能够创建自己的软件包和储存库，然后可以使用这些软件包和储存库来"
"更新您的客户端。它们还使您能够在环境中使用第三方供应商提供的软件。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:3
msgid ""
"This section gives more detail on how to create, administer, and delete "
"custom channels.  You must have administrator privileges to be able to "
"create and manage custom channels."
msgstr ""
"本节提供有关如何创建、管理和删除自定义通道的更多细节。您必须拥有管理员特权才"
"能创建和管理自定义通道。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating Custom Channels and Repositories"
msgstr "创建自定义通道和储存库"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:5
msgid ""
"Before you create a custom channel, determine which base channel you want to "
"associate it with, and which repositories you want to use for content."
msgstr ""
"在创建自定义通道之前，请确定要将其关联到哪个基础通道，以及要为内容使用哪些储"
"存库。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:6
msgid ""
"If you have custom software packages that you need to install on your client "
"systems, you can create a custom child channel to manage them.  You need to "
"create the channel in the {productname} {webui} and create a repository for "
"the packages, before assigning the channel to your systems."
msgstr ""
"如果您需要将自定义软件包安装在客户端系统上，可以创建自定义子通道来管理它们。"
"需要在 {productname} {webui} 中创建通道，并为软件包创建储存库，然后将该通道指"
"派到系统。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:7
msgid ""
"Do not create child channels containing packages that are not compatible "
"with the client system."
msgstr "不要创建其中有软件包与客户端系统不兼容的子通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:8
msgid ""
"You can select a vendor channel as the base channel if you want to use "
"packages provided by a vendor.  Alternatively, select ``none`` to make your "
"custom channel a base channel."
msgstr ""
"如果您要使用供应商提供的软件包，可以选择供应商通道作为基础通道。或者，选择``"
"无``以将自定义通道设为基础通道。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Creating a Custom Channel"
msgstr "过程：创建自定义通道"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:10
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Software[Manage > Channels], "
"and click btn:[Create Channel]."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:软件[管理 > 通道]，然后单击 btn:[创建"
"通道]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:11
msgid ""
"On the [guimenu]``Create Software Channel`` page, give your channel a name "
"(for example, [systemitem]``My Tools SLES 15 SP1 x86_64``) and a label (for "
"example, [systemitem]``my-tools-sles15sp1-x86_64``)."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``创建软件通道``页面上，为您的通道命名（例如 [systemitem]``My "
"Tools SLES 15 SP1 x86_64``）和标签（例如 [systemitem]``my-tools-sles15sp1-"
"x86_64``）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:12
msgid "Labels must not contain spaces or uppercase letters."
msgstr "标签不能包含空格或大写字母。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:13
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Parent Channel`` drop down, choose the relevant base "
"channel (for example, [systemitem]``SLE-Product-SLES15-SP1-Pool for "
"x86_64``)."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``父通道``下拉菜单中选择相关的基础通道（例如 [systemitem]``SLE-"
"Product-SLES15-SP1-Pool for x86_64``）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:14
msgid "Ensure that you choose the compatible parent channel for your packages."
msgstr "确保为软件包选择兼容的父通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:15
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Architecture`` drop down, choose the appropriate hardware "
"architecture (for example, [systemitem]``x86_64``)."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``体系结构``下拉菜单中选择适当的硬件体系结构（例如 "
"[systemitem]``x86_64``）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:16
msgid ""
"Provide any additional information in the contact details, channel access "
"control, and GPG fields, as required for your environment."
msgstr ""
"根据环境的需要，在联系方法细节、通道访问控制和 GPG 字段中提供任何附加信息。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:17
msgid "Click btn:[Create Channel]."
msgstr "单击 btn:[创建通道]。"

#.  We need to create a section on importing GPG keys and change this to point there: https://github.com/SUSE/spacewalk/issues/9474 LKB 2019-09-18
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Custom channels sometimes require additional security settings.  Many third "
"party vendors secure packages with GPG.  If you want to use GPG-protected "
"packages in your custom channel, you need to trust the GPG key which has "
"been used to sign the metadata.  You can then check the [guimenu]``Has "
"Signed Metadata?`` check box to match the package metadata against the "
"trusted GPG keys."
msgstr ""
"自定义通道有时需要额外的安全设置。许多第三方供应商使用 GPG 保护软件包。如果您"
"想要在自定义通道中使用受 GPG 保护的软件包，需要信任用来为元数据签名的 GPG 密"
"钥。然后，可以选中[guimenu]``包含已签名的元数据？``复选框，以将软件包元数据与"
"受信任的 GPG 密钥进行匹配。"

#.  This xref is misleading:
#.  For more information on importing GPG keys, see xref:reference:systems/autoinst-gpg-and-ssl-keys.adoc[].
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:19
msgid ""
"If remote channels and repositories are signed with GPG keys, you can import "
"and trust these GPG keys.  For example, execute the [command]``spacewalk-"
"repo-sync`` from the command line on the {productname} Server:"
msgstr ""
"如果远程通道和储存库已使用 GPG 密钥签名，则您可以导入并信任这些 GPG 密钥。例"
"如，从 {productname} Server 上的命令行执行 [command]``spacewalk-repo-sync``："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "/usr/bin/spacewalk-repo-sync -c <channellabelname> -t yum\n"
msgstr "/usr/bin/spacewalk-repo-sync -c <通道标签名称> -t yum\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:21
msgid ""
"The underlying [command]``zypper`` call will import the key, if it is "
"available.  The {webui} does not offer this feature."
msgstr ""
"基础 [command]``zypper`` 调用将导入密钥（如果已提供）。{webui} 不提供此功能。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:22
msgid ""
"This only works when the repository you want to mirror is set up in a "
"special way and provide the \"key\" in the repository next to the "
"signature.  This is the case for all repositories generated by the Open "
"Build Service (OBS).  For other repositories special preparation steps are "
"needed (see below!)."
msgstr ""
"仅当您要镜像的储存库是以特殊方式设置的，并且储存库中的签名旁边提供了“key”时，"
"才可以正常完成此操作。开放式构建服务 (OBS) 生成的所有储存库都是这种情况。对于"
"其他储存库，需要完成特殊的准备步骤（参见下文！）。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:23
msgid ""
"By default, the ``Enable GPG Check`` field is checked when you create a new "
"channel.  If you would like to add custom packages and applications to your "
"channel, make sure you uncheck this field to be able to install unsigned "
"packages.  Disabling the GPG check is a security risk if packages are from "
"an untrusted source."
msgstr ""
"当您创建新通道时，默认会选中``启用 GPG 检查``字段。如果您要将自定义软件包和应"
"用程序添加到您的通道，请务必取消选中此字段，以便能够安装未签名的软件包。如果"
"软件包来自不受信任的源，则禁用 GPG 检查会带来安全风险。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:24
msgid ""
"If you are registering traditional {rhel}{nbsp}7 or SLES {es}{nbsp}7 clients "
"you might notice errors with unsigned packages.  For more information, see "
"xref:administration:troubleshooting/tshoot-registertradrhel.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"如果您正在注册传统的 {rhel}{nbsp}7 或 SLES {es}{nbsp}7 客户端，有可能会看到未"
"签名软件包的错误。有关详细信息，请参见 xref:administration:troubleshooting/"
"tshoot-registertradrhel.adoc[]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:25
msgid ""
"You can only add a repository to the {productname} with the {webui} if it is "
"a valid software repository.  Check in advance that needed repository "
"metadata are available.  Tools such as [command]``createrepo`` and "
"[command]``reprepro`` are useful in this regard.  [command]``mgr-push`` can "
"help with pushing a single RPM into a channel without creating a "
"repository.  For more information, see the man pages for "
"[literal]``createrepo_c`` and [literal]``reprepro``."
msgstr ""
"仅当储存库是有效的软件储存库时，才能使用 {webui} 将其添加到 {productname}。提"
"前检查是否提供了所需的储存库元数据。可以使用 [command]``createrepo`` 和 "
"[command]``reprepro`` 等工具进行这种检查。[command]``mgr-push`` 可帮助您将单"
"个 RPM 推送到通道，而无需创建储存库。有关详细信息，请参见 "
"[literal]``createrepo_c`` 和 [literal]``reprepro`` 的手册页。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Adding a Software Repository"
msgstr "过程：添加软件储存库"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:27
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Software[Manage > "
"Repositories], and click btn:[Create Repository]."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:软件[管理 > 储存库]，然后单击 btn:[创"
"建储存库]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:28
msgid ""
"On the [guimenu]``Create Repository`` page, give your repository a label "
"(for example, [systemitem]``my-tools-sles15sp1-x86_64-repo``)."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``创建储存库``页面上，为该储存库指定标签（例如 [systemitem]``my-"
"tools-sles15sp1-x86_64-repo``）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:29
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Repository URL`` field, provide the path to the directory "
"that contains the [path]``repodata`` file (for example, "
"[systemitem]``file:///opt/mytools/``).  You can use any valid addressing "
"protocol in this field."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``储存库 URL`` 字段中，提供包含 [path]``repodata`` 文件的目录的路"
"径（例如 [systemitem]``file:///opt/mytools/``）。可以在此字段中使用任何有效寻"
"址协议。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:30
msgid "Uncheck the [guimenu]``Has Signed Metadata?`` check box."
msgstr "取消选中[guimenu]``包含已签名的元数据？``复选框。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:31
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: Complete the SSL fields if your repository requires client "
"certificate authentication."
msgstr "可选：如果您的储存库需要客户端证书身份验证，请填写 SSL 字段。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:32
msgid "Click btn:[Create Repository]."
msgstr "单击 btn:[创建储存库]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:33
msgid ""
"The above procedure only works if the repository you want to mirror provides "
"the \"key\" in the repository next to the signature.  This is the case for "
"all repositories generated by the OBS, but it is typically not the case for "
"other repos of operating systems that are not offered by the OBS."
msgstr ""
"仅当您要镜像的储存库中在签名旁边提供了“key”时，才能正常完成上述过程。OBS 生成"
"的所有储存库都是这种情况，但其他不是由 OBS 提供的操作系统储存库并非如此。"

#.  Not sure how it is possible to import the key into the RPM DB which is used for syncing.
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:34
msgid ""
"If the repository you want to use does not have a GPG key you can provide "
"one yourself and import the GPG key into the keyring manually.  If you "
"import the key into the [path]``/var/lib/spacewalk/gpgdir`` keyring using "
"the [command]``gpg`` commandline tool it would be stored permanently.  The "
"key would also persist if the chroot environment would be cleaned."
msgstr ""
"如果您要使用的储存库不包含 GPG 密钥，您可以自己提供一个 GPG 密钥并手动将其导"
"入密钥环。如果您使用 [command]``gpg`` 命令行工具将密钥导入 [path]``/var/lib/"
"spacewalk/gpgdir`` 密钥环，将永久储存该密钥。即使清理了 chroot 环境，也会持久"
"保存该密钥。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Creating a Software Repository with GPG Key"
msgstr "过程：使用 GPG 密钥创建软件储存库"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:36
msgid "The gpg command to import a key into the pub keyring is:"
msgstr "用于将密钥导入 pub 密钥环的 gpg 命令是："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:37
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gpg --keyring /var/lib/spacewalk/gpgdir  --import /path/to/gpg.key\n"
"gpg --edit-key <keyid>\n"
msgstr ""
"gpg --keyring /var/lib/spacewalk/gpgdir  --import /path/to/gpg.key\n"
"gpg --edit-key <密钥 ID>\n"

#.  Using gpg is horrible. You need to find out the keyid, you need to trust "ultimately" and save the change.
#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:38
msgid ""
"Add Debian non-flat repositories using ``uyuni_suite``, ``uyuni_component``, "
"and ``uyuni_arch`` query parameters."
msgstr ""
"使用 ``uyuni_suite``、``uyuni_component`` 和 ``uyuni_arch`` 查询参数添加 "
"Debian 非平面储存库。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "``uyuni_suite``"
msgstr "``uyuni_suite``"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:40
msgid ""
"is mandatory.  In Debian documentation, this is also known as "
"[literal]``distribution``.  With this parameter you specify the apt source.  "
"Without this parameter the original approach is used.  If the parameter ends "
"with ``/``, the repository is identified as flat."
msgstr ""
"是必需的。在 Debian 文档中，此参数也名为 [literal]``distribution``。使用此参"
"数可以指定 apt 源。如果不提供此参数，则会使用原始方法。如果该参数以 ``/`` 结"
"尾，则会将储存库标识为平面储存库。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "``uyuni_component``"
msgstr "``uyuni_component``"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:42
msgid ""
"is optional.  This parameter can specify only one component.  It is not "
"possible to list the components.  An apt source entry allows to specify "
"multiple components, but for Uyuni it is not possible.  Instead you must "
"create separate repository for each component."
msgstr ""
"是可选的。此参数只能指定一个组件。无法列出组件。一个 apt 源项允许指定多个组"
"件，但对于 Uyuni 无法做到这一点。对此，您必须为每个组件创建单独的储存库。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "``uyuni_arch``"
msgstr "``uyuni_arch``"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:44
msgid ""
"is optional.  If omitted the architecture name is calculated with a SQL "
"query for the channel from the database.  Specify ``uyuni_arch`` explicitly "
"if it does not match the architecture of the channel (sometimes architecture "
"naming is ambiguous)."
msgstr ""
"是可选的。如果将其省略，则会使用 SQL 查询为数据库中的通道计算体系结构名称。如"
"果``uyuni_arch``与通道体系结构不匹配（有时体系结构命名不明确），请显式指定此"
"参数。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:45
msgid "Here are some examples:"
msgstr "下面提供了一些示例："

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:46
#, no-wrap
msgid "Debian non-flat repository mapping"
msgstr "Debian 非平面储存库映射"

#. type: Table
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:47
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Type             | Source line / URL\n"
"| apt source line  | ``deb https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/``\n"
"| URL mapping      | ``https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable?uyuni_suite=binary/``\n"
"| {nbsp}           |\n"
"| apt source line  | ``deb https://deb.debian.org/debian/dists stable main``\n"
"| URL mapping      | ``https://deb.debian.org/debian/dists?uyuni_suite=stable&uyuni_component=main``\n"
msgstr ""
"| 类型             | 源行/URL\n"
"| apt 源行  | ``deb https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/``\n"
"| URL 映射      | ``https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable?uyuni_suite=binary/``\n"
"| {nbsp}           |\n"
"| apt 源行  | ``deb https://deb.debian.org/debian/dists stable main``\n"
"| URL 映射      | ``https://deb.debian.org/debian/dists?uyuni_suite=stable&uyuni_component=main``\n"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:48
msgid ""
"Find here background information about the Debian repository definition "
"format.  This information is based on https://wiki.debian.org/"
"DebianRepository/Format#Overview."
msgstr ""
"在此处查找有关 Debian 储存库定义格式的背景信息。此信息基于 link:https://wiki."
"debian.org/DebianRepository/Format#Overview[]。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:49
msgid "The repository definition format is as follows:"
msgstr "储存库定义格式如下："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "deb uri suite [component1] [component2] [...]\n"
msgstr "deb URI 套件 [组件 1] [组件 2] [...]\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "deb https://deb.debian.org/debian/dists stable main\n"
msgstr "deb https://deb.debian.org/debian/dists stable main\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:53
#: modules/administration/pages/troubleshooting/tshoot-schema-upgrade-fails.adoc:5
msgid "or"
msgstr "或"

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "deb https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/\n"
msgstr "deb https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:55
msgid ""
"For each pair of ``suite`` and ``component`` the spezification defines a "
"distinct URL calculated on the base URL ``+ suite + component``."
msgstr ""
"对于每一对``套件``和``组件``，规范定义了一个根据基 URL ``+ 套件 + 组件``计算"
"的不同 URL。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Assigning the Repository to a Channel"
msgstr "过程：将储存库指派到通道"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:57
msgid ""
"Assign your new repository to your custom channel by navigating to menu:"
"Software[Manage > Channels], clicking the name of your newly created custom "
"channel, and navigating to the [guimenu]``Repositories`` tab."
msgstr ""
"通过导航到menu:软件[管理 > 通道]，单击新建的自定义通道的名称，然后导航到"
"[guimenu]``储存库``选项卡，将新储存库指派到自定义通道。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:58
msgid ""
"Ensure the repository you want to assign to the channel is checked, and "
"click btn:[Update Repositories]."
msgstr "确保选中您要指派到通道的储存库，然后单击 btn:[更新储存库]。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:59
msgid ""
"Navigate to the [guimenu]``Sync`` tab and click btn:[Sync Now] to "
"synchronize immediately. For more information about channel synchronization, "
"see below."
msgstr ""
"导航到[guimenu]``同步``选项卡，然后单击 btn:[立即同步] 立即同步。有关通道同步"
"的详细信息，请参见下文。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Adding Custom Channels to an Activation Key"
msgstr "过程：将自定义通道添加到激活密钥"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:61
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[Activation Keys], and "
"select the key you want to add the custom channel to."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:系统[激活密钥]，然后选择要将自定义通"
"道添加到的密钥。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:62
msgid ""
"On the [guiemnu]``Details`` tab, in the [guimenu]``Child Channels`` listing, "
"select the channel to associate."
msgstr ""
"在[guiemnu]``细节``选项卡上的[guimenu]``子通道``列表中，选择要关联的通道。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:63
msgid "You can select multiple channels, if you need to."
msgstr "如果需要，您可以选择多个通道。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:64
msgid "Click btn:[Update Activation Key]."
msgstr "单击 btn:[更新激活密钥]。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "Custom channel synchronization"
msgstr "自定义通道同步"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:66
msgid ""
"To avoid missing important updates, {suse} recommends to keep your custom "
"channels up to date with the remote repositories changes."
msgstr ""
"为了避免错过重要更新，{suse} 建议通过远程储存库更改来使您的自定义通道保持最"
"新。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:67
msgid ""
"By default, custom channels are not synchronized automatically. In order to "
"keep a custom channel up to date, you need to:"
msgstr ""
"系统默认不会自动同步自定义通道。为了确保自定义通道保持最新状态，您需要："

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:68
msgid ""
"synchronize it manually by navigating to the [guimenu]``Sync`` tab and click "
"btn:[Sync Now],"
msgstr "通过导航到``同步``选项卡并单击 btn:[立即同步] 来手动同步该通道。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:69
msgid ""
"set up an automated synchronization schedule from the "
"[guimenu]``Repositories`` tab."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``储存库``选项卡中设置自动同步日程安排。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:70
msgid ""
"It is also possible to enable automatic synchronization for all the custom "
"channels you create. To do this, set in [path]``/etc/rhn/rhn.conf``:"
msgstr ""
"您也可以为创建的所有自定义通道启用自动同步。要实现此目的，请在 [path]``/etc/"
"rhn/rhn.conf`` 中进行如下设置："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "java.unify_custom_channel_management = 1\n"
msgstr "java.unify_custom_channel_management = 1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:72
msgid ""
"With this property turned on, a synchronization will happen automatically:"
msgstr "启用此属性后，系统将会自动执行一次同步："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:73
msgid ""
"after adding a repository to a channel from the UI or by using "
"[command]``spacewalk-common-channels``"
msgstr ""
"在 UI 中或者使用 [command]``spacewalk-common-channels`` 将储存库添加到通道后"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:74
msgid ""
"as part of the daily task ``mgr-sync-refresh-default``, which will "
"synchronize all your custom and vendor channels."
msgstr ""
"在执行日常任务 ``mgr-sync-refresh-default`` 的过程中，这将同步您的所有自定义"
"通道和供应商通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:75
msgid ""
"When the process is started, there are several ways to check if a channel "
"has finished synchronizing:"
msgstr "该过程开始后，可通过多种方式检查通道是否已完成同步："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:76
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Admin[Setup Wizard] and "
"select the [guimenu]``Products`` tab."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:管理[安装向导]，然后选择[guimenu]``产"
"品``选项卡。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:77
msgid ""
"This dialog displays a completion bar for each product when they are being "
"synchronized."
msgstr "产品同步时，此对话框将为每个产品显示一个完成栏。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:78
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Software[Manage > Channels], "
"then click the channel associated to the repository."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:软件[管理 > 通道]，然后单击与储存库关"
"联的通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:79
msgid ""
"Navigate to the menu:[Repositories > Sync] tab.  The [guimenu]``Sync "
"Status`` is shown next to the repository name.."
msgstr ""
"导航到menu:储存库[同步]选项卡。储存库名称旁边会显示[guimenu]``同步状态``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:80
msgid "Check the synchronization log file at the command prompt:"
msgstr "在命令提示符下检查同步日志文件："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "tail -f /var/log/rhn/reposync/<channel-label>.log\n"
msgstr "tail -f /var/log/rhn/reposync/<channel-label>.log\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:82
msgid ""
"Each child channel generates its own log during the synchronization "
"progress.  You need to check all the base and child channel log files to be "
"sure that the synchronization is complete."
msgstr ""
"每个子通道在同步过程中会生成自身的日志。您需要检查所有基础通道和子通道日志文"
"件，以确保同步完成。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Add Packages and Patches to Custom Channels"
msgstr "将软件包和补丁添加到自定义通道"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:84
msgid ""
"When you create a new custom channel without cloning it from an existing "
"channel, it does not contain any packages or patches.  You can add the "
"packages and patches you require using the {productname} {webui}."
msgstr ""
"如果您创建新的自定义通道但未从现有通道克隆，则创建的通道不包含任何软件包或补"
"丁。可以使用 {productname} {webui} 添加所需的软件包和补丁。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:85
msgid ""
"Custom channels can only include packages or patches that are cloned or "
"custom, and they must match the base architecture of the channel.  Patches "
"added to custom channels must apply to a package that exists in the channel."
msgstr ""
"自定义通道只能包含克隆的或者自定义的软件包或补丁，并且这些软件包或补丁必须与"
"通道的基础体系结构相匹配。添加到自定义通道的补丁必须适用于通道中的软件包。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Adding Packages to Custom Channels"
msgstr "过程：将软件包添加到自定义通道"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:87
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Software[Manage > Channels], "
"and go to the [guimenu]``Packages`` tab."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:软件[管理 > 通道]，然后转到"
"[guimenu]``软件包``选项卡。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:88
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: See all packages currently in the channel by navigating to the "
"[guimenu]``List/Remove`` tab."
msgstr ""
"可选：通过导航到[guimenu]``列出/去除``选项卡查看当前包含在通道中的所有软件"
"包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:89
msgid ""
"Add new packages to the channel by navigating to the [guimenu]``Add`` tab."
msgstr "通过导航到[guimenu]``添加``选项卡将新软件包添加到通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:90
msgid ""
"Select the parent channel to provide packages, and click btn:[View Packages] "
"to populate the list."
msgstr "选择要为其提供软件包的父通道，然后单击 btn:[查看软件包] 以填充列表。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:91
msgid ""
"Check the packages to add to the custom channel, and click btn:[Add "
"Packages]."
msgstr "检查要添加到自定义通道的软件包，然后单击 btn:[添加软件包]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:92
msgid ""
"When you are satisfied with the selection, click btn:[Confirm Addition] to "
"add the packages to the channel."
msgstr "如果您觉得选择合适，请单击 btn:[确认添加] 以将软件包添加到通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:93
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: You can compare the packages in the current channel with those in "
"a different channel by navigating to menu:Software[Manage > Channels], and "
"going to the menu:Packages[Compare] tab."
msgstr ""
"可选：可以通过导航到menu:软件[管理 > 通道]，然后转到menu:软件包[比较]选项卡，"
"将当前通道中的软件包与其他通道中的软件包进行比较。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:94
msgid ""
"To make the two channels the same, click the btn:[Merge Differences] button, "
"and resolve any conflicts."
msgstr "要使两个通道相同，请单击 btn:[合并差异] 按钮，然后解决任何冲突。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:95
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Adding Patches to a Custom Channel"
msgstr "过程：将补丁添加到自定义通道"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:96
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Software[Manage > Channels], "
"and go to the [guimenu]``Patches`` tab."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:软件[管理 > 通道]，然后转到"
"[guimenu]``补丁``选项卡。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:97
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: See all patches currently in the channel by navigating to the "
"[guimenu]``List/Remove`` tab."
msgstr ""
"可选：通过导航到[guimenu]``列出/去除``选项卡查看当前包含在通道中的所有补丁。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:98
msgid ""
"Add new patches to the channel by navigating to the [guimenu]``Add`` tab, "
"and selecting what kind of patches you want to add."
msgstr ""
"通过导航到[guimenu]``添加``选项卡，然后选择要添加的补丁类型，将新补丁添加到通"
"道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:99
msgid ""
"Select the parent channel to provide patches, and click btn:[View Associated "
"Patches] to populate the list."
msgstr "选择要为其提供补丁的父通道，然后单击 btn:[浏览关联补丁] 以填充列表。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:100
msgid ""
"Check the patches to add to the custom channel, and click btn:[Confirm]."
msgstr "检查要添加到自定义通道的补丁，然后单击 btn:[确认]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:101
msgid ""
"When you are satisfied with the selection, click btn:[Confirm] to add the "
"patches to the channel."
msgstr "如果您觉得选择合适，请单击 btn:[确认] 以将补丁添加到通道。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:102
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manage Custom Channels"
msgstr "管理自定义通道"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:103
msgid ""
"{productname} administrators and channel administrators can alter or delete "
"any channel."
msgstr "{productname} 管理员和通道管理员可以更改或删除任何通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:104
msgid ""
"To grant other users rights to alter or delete a channel, navigate to menu:"
"Software[Manage > Channels] and select the channel you want to edit.  "
"Navigate to the [guimenu]``Managers`` tab, and check the user to grant "
"permissions.  Click btn:[Update] to save the changes."
msgstr ""
"要授予其他用户更改或删除通道的权限，请导航到menu:软件[管理 > 通道]，然后选择"
"要编辑的通道。导航到[guimenu]``管理者``选项卡，并选中要向其授予权限的用户。单"
"击 btn:[更新] 以保存更改。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:105
msgid ""
"If you delete a channel that has been assigned to a set of clients, it "
"triggers an immediate update of the channel state for any clients associated "
"with the deleted channel.  This is to ensure that the changes are reflected "
"accurately in the repository file."
msgstr ""
"如果您删除某个已指派到一组客户端的通道，与已删除通道关联的任何客户端的通道状"
"态将立即更新。这是为了确保在储存库文件中准确反映所做的更改。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:106
msgid ""
"You cannot delete {productname} channels with the {webui}.  Only custom "
"channels can be deleted."
msgstr "无法使用 {webui} 删除 {productname} 通道。只能删除自定义通道。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Deleting Custom Channels"
msgstr "过程：删除自定义通道"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:108
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Software[Manage > Channels], "
"and select the channel you want to delete."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:软件[管理 > 通道]，然后选择要删除的通"
"道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:109
msgid "Click btn:[Delete software channel]."
msgstr "单击 btn:[删除软件通道]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:110
msgid ""
"On the [guimenu]``Delete Channel`` page, check the details of the channel "
"you are deleting, and check the [guimenu]``Unsubscribe Systems`` checkbox to "
"remove the custom channel from any systems that might still be subscribed."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``删除通道``页面上，检查您要删除的通道的细节，然后选中[guimenu]``"
"取消订阅系统``复选框，以从任何可能仍已订阅的系统中去除该自定义通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:111
msgid "Click btn:[Delete Channel]."
msgstr "单击 btn:[删除通道]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:112
msgid ""
"When channels are deleted, the packages that are part of the deleted channel "
"are not automatically removed.  You are not able to update packages that "
"have had their channel deleted."
msgstr ""
"删除通道时，不会自动去除其中的软件包。您无法更新其通道已被删除的软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/custom-channels.adoc:113
msgid ""
"You can delete packages that are not associated with a channel in the "
"{productname} {webui}.  Navigate to menu:Software[Manage > Packages], check "
"the packages to remove, and click btn:[Delete Packages]."
msgstr ""
"可以在 {productname} {webui} 中删除与通道没有关联的软件包。导航到menu:软件[管"
"理 > 软件包]，选中要去除的软件包，然后单击 btn:[删除软件包]。"

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Disconnected Setup"
msgstr "断开连接的设置"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:2
msgid ""
"When it is not possible to connect {productname} to the internet, you can "
"use it within a disconnected environment."
msgstr "无法将 {productname} 连接到互联网时，您可以在断开连接的环境中使用它。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:3
msgid ""
"The repository mirroring tool (RMT) is available on {sle}{nbsp}15 and "
"later.  RMT replaces the subscription management tool (SMT), which can be "
"used on older {sle} installations."
msgstr ""
"在 {sle}{nbsp}15 和更高版本上可以使用储存库镜像工具 (RMT)。RMT 取代了订阅管理"
"工具 (SMT)，后者在较旧的 {sle} 安装中可用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:4
msgid ""
"In a disconnected {productname} setup, RMT or SMT uses an external network "
"to connect to {scc}.  All software channels and repositories are "
"synchronized to a removable storage device.  The storage device can then be "
"used to update the disconnected {productname} installation."
msgstr ""
"在断开连接的 {productname} 设置中，RMT 或 SMT 使用外部网络连接到 {scc}。所有"
"软件通道和储存库会同步到可卸储存设备。然后可以使用该储存设备更新断开连接的 "
"{productname} 安装。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:5
msgid ""
"This setup allows your {productname} installation to remain in an offline, "
"disconnected environment."
msgstr "此设置可让您的 {productname} 安装保留在断开连接的脱机环境中。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Your RMT or SMT instance must be used to manage the {productname} Server "
"directly.  It cannot be used to manage a second RMT or SMT instance, in a "
"cascade."
msgstr ""
"您的 RMT 或 SMT 实例必须用于直接管理 {productname} Server。它不能用于管理级联"
"的另一个 RMT 或 SMT 实例。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:7
msgid ""
"For more information on RMT, see https://documentation.suse.com/sles/15-SP3/"
"html/SLES-all/book-rmt.html."
msgstr ""
"有关 RMT 的详细信息，请参见 link:https://documentation.suse.com/sles/15-SP3/"
"html/SLES-all/book-rmt.html[]。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Synchronize RMT"
msgstr "同步 RMT"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:9
msgid ""
"You can use RMT on {sle} 15 installations to manage clients running {sle} 12 "
"or later."
msgstr ""
"可以在 {sle} 15 安装中使用 RMT 来管理运行 {sle} 12 或更高版本的客户端。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:10
msgid ""
"We recommend you set up a dedicated RMT instance for each {productname} "
"installation."
msgstr "我们建议您为每个 {productname} 安装设置一个专用 RMT 实例。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Setting up RMT"
msgstr "过程：设置 RMT"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:12
msgid "On the RMT instance, install the RMT package:"
msgstr "在 RMT 实例上安装 RMT 软件包："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "zypper in rmt-server\n"
msgstr "zypper in rmt-server\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:14
msgid "Configure RMT using {yast}:"
msgstr "使用 {yast} 配置 RMT："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "yast2 rmt\n"
msgstr "yast2 rmt\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:16
msgid "Follow the prompts to complete installation."
msgstr "按照提示完成安装。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:17
msgid ""
"For more information on setting up RMT, see https://documentation.suse.com/"
"sles/15-SP3/html/SLES-all/book-rmt.html."
msgstr ""
"有关设置 RMT 的详细信息，请参见 link:https://documentation.suse.com/sles/15-"
"SP3/html/SLES-all/book-rmt.html[]。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Synchronizing RMT with SCC"
msgstr "过程：将 RMT 与 SCC 同步"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:19
msgid ""
"On the RMT instance, list all available products and repositories for your "
"organization:"
msgstr "在 RMT 实例上，列出您的组织可用的所有产品和储存库："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rmt-cli products list --all\n"
"rmt-cli repos list --all\n"
msgstr ""
"rmt-cli products list --all\n"
"rmt-cli repos list --all\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:21
msgid "Synchronize all available updates for your organization:"
msgstr "同步您的组织可用的所有更新："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "rmt-cli sync\n"
msgstr "rmt-cli sync\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:23
msgid "You can also configure RMT to synchronize regularly using systemd."
msgstr "还可以使用 systemd 将 RMT 配置为定期同步。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:24
msgid "Enable the products you require."
msgstr "启用所需的产品。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:25
msgid "For example, to enable SLES 15:"
msgstr "例如，要启用 SLES 15，请运行以下命令："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "rmt-cli product enable sles/15/x86_64\n"
msgstr "rmt-cli product enable sles/15/x86_64\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:27
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:40
msgid "Export the synchronized data to your removable storage."
msgstr "将已同步的数据导出到可卸储存。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:28
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:41
msgid "In this example, the storage medium is mounted at [path]``/mnt/usb``:"
msgstr "在此示例中，储存媒体的挂载位置为 [path]``/mnt/usb``："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "rmt-cli export data /mnt/usb\n"
msgstr "rmt-cli export data /mnt/usb\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:30
msgid "Export the enabled repositories to your removable storage:"
msgstr "将已启用的储存库导出到可卸储存："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/disconnected-setup.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
