#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Organizations"
msgstr "组织"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Organizations are used to manage user access and permissions within "
"{productname}."
msgstr "组织用于管理 {productname} 中的用户访问权限和许可权限。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:3
msgid ""
"For most environments, a single organization is enough.  However, more "
"complicated environments might need several organizations.  You might like "
"to have an organization for each physical location within your business, or "
"for different business functions."
msgstr ""
"对于大多数环境而言，一个组织便已足够。但是，较复杂的环境可能需要多个组织。您"
"可以为企业中的每个物理位置或不同的业务职能创建一个组织。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:4
msgid ""
"When you have created your organizations, you can create and assign users to "
"your organizations.  You can then assign permissions on an organization "
"level, which applies by default to every user assigned to the organization."
msgstr ""
"创建组织后，可以创建用户并将其指派到组织。然后，可以在组织级别指派权限，这些"
"权限默认将应用于指派到组织的每个用户。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:5
msgid ""
"You can also configure authentication methods for your new organization, "
"including PAM and single sign-on.  For more information about "
"authentication, see xref:administration:auth-methods.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"您还可以为新组织配置身份验证方法，包括 PAM 和单点登录。有关身份验证的详细信"
"息，请参见 xref:administration:auth-methods.adoc[]。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Creating a New Organization"
msgstr "过程：创建新组织"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:8
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Admin[Organizations], and "
"click btn:[Create Organization]."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:管理[组织]，然后单击 btn:[创建组织]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:9
msgid "In the [guimenu]``Create Organization`` dialog, complete these fields:"
msgstr "在[guimenu]``创建组织``对话框中填写以下字段："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:10
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Organization Name`` field, type a name for your new "
"organization."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``组织名称``字段中，键入新组织的名称。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:11
msgid "The name should be between 3 and 128 characters long."
msgstr "该名称的长度应为 3 到 128 个字符。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:12
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Desired Login`` field, type the login name you want to use "
"for the organization's administrator."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``要使用的登录名``字段中，键入要用于组织管理员的登录名。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:13
msgid ""
"This must be a new administrator account, you are not be able to use an "
"existing administrator account to sign in to the new organization, including "
"the one you are currently signed in with."
msgstr ""
"这必须是一个新的管理员帐户，您无法使用现有的管理员帐户（包括当前使用的登录帐"
"户）登录到新组织。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:14
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Desired Password`` field, type a password for the new "
"organization's administrator."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``要使用的口令``字段中，键入新组织管理员的口令。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Confirm the password by typing it again in the [guimenu]``Confirm Password`` "
"field.  Password strength is indicated by the colored bar beneath the "
"password fields."
msgstr ""
"在[guimenu]``确认口令``字段中再次键入该口令以确认。口令强度由口令字段下方的彩"
"色条指示。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:16
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Email`` field, type an email address for the new "
"organization's administrator."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``电子邮件``字段中，键入新组织管理员的电子邮件地址。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:17
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``First Name`` field, select a salutation, and type a given "
"name for the new organization's administrator."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``名字``字段中选择一种称呼，然后键入新组织管理员的名字。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:18
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Last Name`` field, type a surname for the new "
"organization's administrator."
msgstr "在[guimenu]``姓氏``字段中，键入新组织管理员的姓氏。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:19
msgid "Click btn:[Create Organization]."
msgstr "单击 btn:[创建组织]。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manage Organizations"
msgstr "管理组织"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:21
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Admin[Organizations] to see a "
"list of available organizations.  Click the name of an organization to "
"manage it."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:管理[组织]可查看可用组织的列表。单击"
"某个组织的名称可对其进行管理。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:22
msgid ""
"From the menu:Admin[Organizations] section, you can access tabs to manage "
"users, trusts, configuration, and states for your organization."
msgstr ""
"在menu:管理[组织]部分，可以访问相应的选项卡来管理组织的用户、信任、配置和状"
"态。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:23
msgid ""
"Organizations can only be managed by their administrators.  To manage an "
"organization, ensure you are signed in as the correct administrator for the "
"organization you want to change."
msgstr ""
"组织只能由其管理员管理。要管理组织，请确保以您要更改的组织的正确管理员身份登"
"录。"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Organization Users"
msgstr "组织用户"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:25
msgid ""
"Navigate to the [guimenu]``Users`` tab to view the list of all users "
"associated with the organization, and their role.  Clicking a username takes "
"you to the [guimenu]``Users`` menu to add, change, or delete users."
msgstr ""
"导航到[guimenu]``用户``选项卡可查看与组织关联的所有用户的列表及其角色。单击某"
"个用户名会转到[guimenu]``用户``菜单，可在其中添加、更改或删除用户。"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Trusted Organizations"
msgstr "受信任组织"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:27
msgid ""
"Navigate to the [guimenu]``Trusts`` tab to add or remove trusted "
"organizations.  Establishing trust between organizations allow them to share "
"content between them, and gives you the ability to transfer clients from one "
"organization to another."
msgstr ""
"导航到[guimenu]``信任``选项卡可添加或去除受信任组织。在组织之间建立信任可让它"
"们相互共享内容，这样您也可以在不同的组织之间切换客户端。"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure Organizations"
msgstr "配置组织"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:29
msgid ""
"Navigate to the [guimenu]``Configuration`` tab to manage the configuration "
"of your organization.  This includes the use of staged contents, and the use "
"of SCAP files."
msgstr ""
"导航到[guimenu]``配置``选项卡可以管理组织的配置。这包括使用暂存内容和使用 "
"SCAP 文件。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:30
msgid ""
"For more information about content staging, see xref:administration:content-"
"staging.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"有关内容暂存的详细信息，请参见 xref:administration:content-staging.adoc[]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:31
msgid ""
"For more information about OpenSCAP, see xref:reference:audit/audit-openscap-"
"overview.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"有关 OpenSCAP 的详细信息，请参见 xref:reference:audit/audit-openscap-"
"overview.adoc[]。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manage States"
msgstr "管理状态"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:33
msgid ""
"Navigate to the [guimenu]``States`` tab to manage Salt states for all "
"clients in your organization.  States allow you to define global security "
"policies, or add a common admin user to all clients."
msgstr ""
"导航到[guimenu]``状态``选项卡可以管理组织中所有客户端的 Salt 状态。使用状态可"
"以定义全局安全策略，或者将公共管理员用户添加到所有客户端。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:34
msgid ""
"For more information about Salt States, see xref:specialized-guides:salt/"
"salt-states-and-pillars.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"有关 Salt 状态的详细信息，请参见 xref:specialized-guides:salt/salt-states-"
"and-pillars.adoc[]。"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manage Configuration Channels"
msgstr "管理配置通道"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:36
msgid ""
"You can select which configuration channels should be applied across your "
"organization.  Configuration channels can be created in the {productname} "
"{webui} by navigating to menu:Configuration[Channels].  Apply configuration "
"channels to your organization using the {productname} {webui}."
msgstr ""
"可以选择要在整个组织中应用哪些配置通道。可以在 {productname} {webui} 中导航到"
"menu:配置[通道]来创建配置通道。使用 {productname} {webui} 将配置通道应用于您"
"的组织。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Applying Configuration Channels to an Organization"
msgstr "过程：将配置通道应用于组织"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:38
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Home[My Organization > "
"Configuration Channels]."
msgstr "在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:首页[我的组织 > 配置通道]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:39
msgid "Use the search feature to locate a channel by name."
msgstr "使用搜索功能按名称查找通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:40
msgid "Check the channel to be applied and click btn:[Save Changes]."
msgstr "选中要应用的通道，然后单击 btn:[保存更改]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:41
msgid ""
"This saves to the database, but does not apply the changes to the channel."
msgstr "这会将更改保存到数据库，但不会将其应用于通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:42
msgid "Apply the changes by clicking btn:[Apply]."
msgstr "单击 btn:[应用] 以应用更改。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/organizations.adoc:43
msgid ""
"This schedules the task to apply the changes to all clients within the "
"organization."
msgstr "随即会安排将更改应用于组织中的所有客户端的任务。"

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Patch Management"
msgstr "补丁管理"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:2
msgid "This chapter contains various topics related to patch management."
msgstr "本章包含有关补丁管理的各个主题。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Retracted Patches"
msgstr "已收回补丁"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:4
msgid ""
"When a new patch gets released by the vendor, it might happen that the patch "
"has undesirable side effects (security, stability) in some scenario that was "
"not identified by testing. When this happens (very rarely), vendors "
"typically release a new patch, which may take hours or days, depending on "
"the internal processes in place by that vendor."
msgstr ""
"在供应商发布某个新补丁后，该补丁在某种情况下可能会产生不利的负面影响（在安全"
"性、稳定性方面），而这种情况并未通过测试识别出来。如果出现这种情况（非常罕"
"见），供应商通常会发布新补丁，此过程可能需要数小时甚至数日时间，具体取决于该"
"供应商实施的内部流程。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:5
msgid ""
"SUSE has introduced a new mechanism (2021) called \"retracted patches\" to "
"revoke such patches almost immediately by setting their advisory status to "
"\"retracted\" (instead of \"final\" or \"stable\")."
msgstr ""
"SUSE 引入了一个称为``已收回补丁``的新机制 (2021)，可以通过将此类补丁的建议状"
"态设置为``已收回``（而不是``最终``或``稳定``）来近实时地撤消这些补丁。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:6
msgid ""
"A patch is \"retracted,\" when its advisory status attribute is set to "
"\"retracted.\" A package is \"retracted,\" when it belongs to a "
"\"retracted\" patch."
msgstr ""
"如果某个补丁的建议状态属性设置为 ``retracted``，则会``收回``该补丁。如果某个"
"软件包属于``已收回``的补丁，则会``收回``该软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:7
msgid ""
"A retracted patch or package cannot be installed on systems with "
"{productname}. The only way to install a retracted package, is to do it "
"manually with [literal]``zypper install`` and specifying the exact package "
"version.  For example:"
msgstr ""
"无法在包含 {productname} 的系统上安装已收回的补丁或软件包。安装已收回软件包的"
"唯一方法是使用 [literal]``zypper install`` 并指定确切的软件包版本来手动安装。"
"例如："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "zypper install vim-8.0.1568-5.14.1\n"
msgstr "zypper install vim-8.0.1568-5.14.1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Retracted status of patches and packages is depicted with the icon:times-"
"circle[role=\"red\"] icon in the {webui} of {productname}. For example, see:"
msgstr ""
"{productname} {webui} 中的 icon:times-circle[role=\"red\"] 图标描绘了补丁和软"
"件包的已收回状态。例如，查看："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:10
msgid "list of packages in a channel"
msgstr "通道中软件包的列表"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:11
msgid "list of patches in a channel"
msgstr "通道中补丁的列表"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:12
msgid ""
"When a patch or package, that has been installed on a system, gets "
"retracted, the icon:times-circle[role=\"red\"] icon is also displayed in the "
"installed packages list of that system. {productname} does not provide a way "
"to downgrade such a patch or package."
msgstr ""
"收回安装在系统上的补丁或软件包时，icon:times-circle[role=\"red\"] 图标也会显"
"示在该系统的已安装软件包列表中。{productname} 不提供降级此类补丁或软件包的方"
"法。"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Channel Clones"
msgstr "通道克隆"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:14
msgid ""
"When using cloned channels, you must pay attention to the propagation of the "
"retracted advisory status from the original channels to the clones."
msgstr "使用克隆的通道时，必须小心将原始通道的已收回建议状态传播到克隆版本。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Upon cloning vendor channels into your organization, channel patches will be "
"cloned as well."
msgstr "将供应商通道克隆到组织中时，也会克隆通道补丁。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:16
msgid ""
"When the vendor retracts a patch in a channel and {productname} synchronizes "
"this channel (for example, with the nightly job), the \"retracted\" "
"attribute will not get propagated to the cloned patches and will not be "
"observed by the clients subscribed to cloned channels. To propagate the "
"attribute to your cloned channels use one of the following ways:"
msgstr ""
"当供应商收回通道中的补丁并且 {productname} 同步此通道（例如，通过夜间作业）"
"时，``retracted`` 属性不会传播到克隆的补丁，并且订阅克隆通道的客户端看不到该"
"属性。要将该属性传播到克隆的通道，请使用以下方法之一："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Patch Sync (menu:Software[Manage > cloned channel > Patches > Sync]). This "
"function allows you to align the attributes of patches in your cloned "
"channel to their originals."
msgstr ""
"补丁同步（menu:软件[管理 > 克隆的通道 > 补丁 > 同步]）。使用此功能可使克隆通"
"道中补丁的属性与其原始通道保持一致。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Content Lifecycle Management. For more information about cloned channels in "
"the context of Content Lifecycle Management, see xref:client-configuration:"
"channels.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"内容生命周期管理。有关内容生命周期管理上下文中克隆的通道的详细信息，请参见 "
"xref:client-configuration:channels.adoc[]。"

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Patch sharing"
msgstr "补丁共享"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:20
msgid ""
"When you create multiple vendor channel clones in your organization, the "
"patches are not cloned multiple times, but are shared between cloned "
"channels. As a consequence, when you synchronize your cloned patch (either "
"using the patch sync function or with Content Lifecycle Management mentioned "
"above), all channels using the cloned patch will observe that change."
msgstr ""
"当您在组织中创建多个供应商通道克隆版本时，补丁不会克隆多次，而是在克隆的通道"
"之间共享。因此，当您同步克隆的补丁时（使用补丁同步功能或上面提到的内容生命周"
"期管理），使用该克隆补丁的所有通道都会看到这种变化。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "示例："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:22
msgid ""
"Consider two Content Lifecycle Management projects [literal]``prj1`` and "
"[literal]``prj2``"
msgstr "假设有两个内容生命周期管理项目：[literal]``prj1`` 和 [literal]``prj2``"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:23
msgid ""
"Both of these projects have 2 environments [literal]``dev`` and "
"[literal]``test``"
msgstr "这两个项目都有 2 个环境：[literal]``dev`` 和 [literal]``test``"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:24
msgid "Both of these projects have a vendor channel set as a source channel"
msgstr "这两个项目都有一个设置为源通道的供应商通道"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:25
msgid ""
"All channels in this scenario (four cloned channels in total) are aligned to "
"the latest state of the vendor channels"
msgstr "此场景中的所有通道（总共四个克隆的通道）与供应商通道的最新状态相一致"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:26
msgid ""
"Vendor retracts a patch in the source channel and the nighly job "
"synchronizes it to your {productname}"
msgstr "供应商收回源通道中的某个补丁，夜间作业将此补丁同步到 {productname}"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:27
msgid ""
"None of the four channels see this change because they are using a patch "
"clone, not the patch directly."
msgstr ""
"四个通道都看不到这种变化，因为它们使用的是补丁克隆版本，而不是直接使用该补"
"丁。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/patch-management.adoc:28
msgid ""
"As soon as you synchronize your patch (either you build any of these two "
"projects, or you use the Patch Sync function on any of the four cloned "
"channels), due to the patch sharing, *ALL* of the cloned channels will see "
"the patch as retracted."
msgstr ""
"在您同步补丁（构建这两个项目中的任何一个，或者对四个克隆通道中的任何一个使用"
"补丁同步功能）后，由于补丁共享的原因，*所有*克隆的通道都会发现该补丁已收回。"

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using PTFs in {productname}"
msgstr "在 {productname} 中使用 PTF"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:2
msgid ""
"SUSE provides temporary fixes for all currently supported solutions shipped "
"directly to its customers.  These PTFs (Program Temporary Fixes) are now "
"available as repositories, which can be synced in {productname}."
msgstr ""
"SUSE 为目前支持的所有解决方案提供直接交付给客户的临时修复。这些 PTF（程序临时"
"修复）现在以储存库的形式提供，后者可在 {productname} 中同步。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Understanding PTF packages"
msgstr "了解 PTF 软件包"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:4
msgid ""
"PTF packages are installed via a proxy package and are named `ptf-xxxxxx`, "
"where xxxxxx is a number and part of the name of the package, not its "
"version."
msgstr ""
"PTF 软件包通过代理软件包安装，命名为 `ptf-xxxxxx`。其中 xxxxxx 是软件包的编号"
"和名称部分，而不是版本。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:5
msgid ""
"They will depend on the correct version of the package that is known to "
"include the correction in the software.  This type of package:"
msgstr "它们取决于已知包含软件中的修正的软件包正确版本。这种软件包："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:6
msgid ""
"cannot be installed accidentally (i.e. zypper update will never suggest "
"installing them),"
msgstr "不可能意外安装（即 zypper 更新绝不会建议安装它们），"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:7
msgid ""
"cannot be removed accidentally (i.e. a newer package version will not "
"replace the PTF one, unless the user makes it explicitly on the zypper "
"command line),"
msgstr ""
"不可能意外去除（即更新的软件包版本不会替换 PTF 软件包，除非用户在 zypper 命令"
"行上明确指示替换），"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:8
msgid ""
"is only updated when the newer version is known to address the specific "
"issue previously solved by the PTF,"
msgstr "仅会在已知有更新版本可解决该 PTF 之前所解决的特定问题时更新，"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:9
msgid ""
"updates only packages already installed on the system (i.e. if a software is "
"split into multiple packages, the PTF will replace only those currently "
"installed on the system)."
msgstr ""
"仅会在系统上已安装软件包时更新（也就是说，如果软件拆分成多个软件包，该 PTF 仅"
"会替换系统上目前安装的那些软件包）。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:10
msgid ""
"The correct ID of the package will be provided by SUSE Support during the "
"course of the support case investigation, along with instruction on how to "
"deploy/restart the affected services."
msgstr ""
"软件包的正确 ID 将由 SUSE 支持团队在进行支持案例调查期间提供，同时还会提供有"
"关如何部署/重启动受影响服务的说明。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing PTF packages"
msgstr "安装 PTF 软件包"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:12
msgid ""
"PTF packages are currently only supported for SLE 12 and SLE 15 based "
"systems.  Other versions or Operating Systems do not have this feature yet "
"and the pages are not visible for them."
msgstr ""
"PTF 软件包目前仅受基于 SLE 12 和 SLE 15 的系统支持。其他版本或操作系统尚不提"
"供此功能，因此未显示与其对应的页面。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Enable and Synchronize PTF repositories using the command line"
msgstr "过程：使用命令行启用和同步 PTF 储存库"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:14
msgid "On the console enter [command]``mgr-sync refresh``."
msgstr "在控制台上输入 [command]``mgr-sync refresh``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Enter [command]``mgr-sync list channel`` and look for channels starting with "
"your SCC account name and `ptfs` in its name.  E.g. `a123456-sles-15.3-ptfs-"
"x86_64`."
msgstr ""
"输入 [command]``mgr-sync list channel``，然后查找以您的 SCC 帐户名称开头且名"
"称中包含 `ptfs` 的通道。例如 `a123456-sles-15.3-ptfs-x86_64`。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:16
msgid "Enable the PTF channel with [command]``mgr-sync add channel <label>``."
msgstr "使用 [command]``mgr-sync add channel <标签>`` 启用该 PTF 通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:17
msgid ""
"This channel is now available and can be added to every system which is "
"using the same base channel."
msgstr "此通道现在便可供使用，并可添加到使用相同基础通道的每个系统。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:18
msgid ""
"PTF packages need to be installed explicitly, since they are not "
"automatically picked up when updating a system.  The SUSE Customer Support "
"will provide the PTF number to fix a specific problem.  The proxy package "
"can be identified in the PTF list with the number.  Every system with PTFs "
"available for installation has a page in {productname} {webui} which lists "
"them."
msgstr ""
"您需要明确安装 PTF 软件包，因为在更新系统时它们不会自动被选中。SUSE 客户支持"
"团队将提供用于修复特定问题的 PTF 编号。可以使用该编号在 PTF 列表中标识该代理"
"软件包。{productname} {webui} 中会针对有可供安装的 PTF 的每个系统显示一个页面"
"来列出这些 PTF。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Enable and Synchronize PTF repositories via the {productname} {webui}"
msgstr "过程：通过 {productname} {webui} 启用和同步 PTF 储存库"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:20
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Admin[Setup Wizard > "
"Products] and look for the product you want to enable the PTF repository for."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:管理[安装向导 > 产品]，然后查找要为其"
"启用 PTF 储存库的产品。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:21
msgid "Click btn:[Show product's channels] next to the products sync status."
msgstr "单击产品同步状态旁边的 btn:[显示产品的通道]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:22
msgid ""
"You should see a popup listing mandatory and optional channels for the "
"product."
msgstr "您应该会看到一个弹出窗口，其中会列出该产品的必需和可选通道。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:23
msgid ""
"In the optional channels list look for channels starting with your SCC "
"account name and `ptfs` in its name.  E.g. [literal]``a123456-sles-15.3-ptfs-"
"x86_64``."
msgstr ""
"在可选通道列表中，查找以您的 SCC 帐户名称开头且名称中包含 `ptfs` 的通道。例"
"如 [literal]``a123456-sles-15.3-ptfs-x86_64``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:24
msgid ""
"Select the channel using the checkbox next to its name and click btn:"
"[Confirm] to schedule the synchronization."
msgstr "使用该通道名称旁边的复选框将其选中，然后单击 btn:[确认] 安排同步。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:25
msgid ""
"Note that the product has to be installed to be able to add optional "
"channels to it."
msgstr "请注意，必须安装该产品才能为其添加可选通道。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Installation of PTF packages"
msgstr "过程：安装 PTF 软件包"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:27
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[Systems List] and "
"select the client where you want to install a PTF."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:系统[系统列表]，然后选择要安装 PTF 的"
"客户端。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:28
msgid ""
"Navigate to the menu:Systems[Software > Packages > Software Channels] and "
"select the [systemitem]``PTF channel``."
msgstr ""
"导航到menu:系统[软件 > 软件包 > 软件通道]，然后选择 [systemitem]``PTF 通道"
"``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:29
msgid ""
"Click btn:[Next], and [guimenu]``Confirm Software Channel Change`` with btn:"
"[Confirm]."
msgstr ""
"单击 btn:[下一步]，然后单击 btn:[确认] 以[guimenu]``确认软件通道更改``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:30
msgid ""
"Navigate to menu:Systems[Events > History] to see the results to check if "
"the channel assignment is finished."
msgstr "导航到menu:系统[事件 > 历史记录]查看结果，确定是否已完成通道指派。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:31
msgid "Navigate to the menu:Systems[Software > PTFs > Install] sub tab."
msgstr "导航到menu:系统[软件 > PTF > 安装]子选项卡。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:32
msgid "Select the PTF package you want to install."
msgstr "选择要安装的 PTF 软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:33
msgid ""
"Click btn:[Install PTF], and [guimenu]``Confirm Program Temporary Fixes "
"(PTFs) Installation`` with btn:[Confirm]."
msgstr ""
"单击 btn:[安装 PTF]，然后单击 btn:[确认] 以[guimenu]``确认安装程序临时修复 "
"(PTF)``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:34
msgid ""
"Navigate to menu:Systems[Events > History] to see PTF installation results."
msgstr "导航到menu:系统[事件 > 历史记录]查看 PTF 安装结果。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:35
msgid ""
"In case a PTF should be installed using the API, the normal "
"[systemitem]``system.schedulePackageInstall`` API can be used with the proxy "
"package name."
msgstr ""
"如果应使用 API 安装 PTF，可以使用常规 [systemitem]``system."
"schedulePackageInstall`` API 和代理软件包名称。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "After PTF installation"
msgstr "安装 PTF 后"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:37
msgid ""
"Once a PTF is confirmed to address the reported issue, the updated package "
"will be tracked for inclusion into a future maintenance update before being "
"widely distributed as a regular maintenance update in the update "
"repositories."
msgstr ""
"一旦确认使用某个 PTF 来解决报告的问题，在将更新的软件包作为更新储存库中的常规"
"维护更新广泛分发之前，需对其进行跟踪，以便在将来的维护更新中纳入该软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:38
msgid ""
"When this regular update with the fix is released, an updated version of the "
"PTF will also be released into the account-specific PTF repository.  The "
"updated PTF will remove the strict dependencies and allow updates to be "
"installed again."
msgstr ""
"在发布包含修复的此常规更新时，还会将 PTF 的一个更新版本发布到特定于帐户的 "
"PTF 储存库中。更新的 PTF 将会解除严格的依赖关系，并允许再次安装更新。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:39
msgid ""
"The replacement of the PTF with the maintenance update which includes the "
"fix happens automatically via a standard package update or patch "
"installation."
msgstr "通过标准软件包更新或补丁安装可自动将 PTF 替换为包含该修复的维护更新。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "Removing the patched version of a package"
msgstr "去除软件包的已修补版本"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:41
msgid ""
"In cases where a PTF needs to be uninstalled and the non-patched version of "
"the packages need to be installed on the system, a simple package remove "
"cannot be used.  The PTF package is not selectable in the standard package "
"list page."
msgstr ""
"如果需要在系统上卸装某个 PTF 并安装软件包的未修补版本，仅执行软件包去除流程无"
"法实现这个目标。在标准软件包列表页面中，无法选择该 PTF 软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:42
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[Systems List] and "
"select the client you want to remove a PTF from."
msgstr ""
"在 {productname} {webui} 中，导航到menu:系统[系统列表]，然后选择要去除 PTF 的"
"客户端。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:43
msgid "Navigate to the menu:Systems[Software > PTFs > List/Remove] sub tab."
msgstr "导航到menu:系统[软件 > PTF > 列出/去除]子选项卡。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:44
msgid "Select the PTF package you want to remove."
msgstr "选择要去除的 PTF 软件包。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:45
msgid ""
"Click btn:[Remove PTFs], and on the [guimenu]``Confirm Program Temporary "
"Fixes (PTFs) Removal`` page click btn:[Confirm]."
msgstr ""
"单击 btn:[去除 PTF]，然后在[guimenu]``确认去除程序临时修复 (PTF)`` 页面上单"
"击 btn:[确认]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:46
msgid "To see the results, navigate to menu:Systems[Events > History]."
msgstr "要查看结果，请导航到menu:系统[事件 > 历史记录]。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:47
msgid ""
"Removing PTFs requires a special version of [literal]``libzypp`` and "
"[literal]``zypper`` to be installed on the client system.  Check "
"[command]``zypper --help`` to confirm whether [command]``removeptf`` is "
"supported.  The [literal]``List/Remove`` tab is only visible if this "
"condition is met."
msgstr ""
"要去除 PTF，需要在客户端系统上安装 [literal]``libzypp`` 和 "
"[literal]``zypper`` 的特殊版本。请运行 [command]``zypper --help`` 确认是否支"
"持 [command]``removeptf``。仅当满足此条件时，[literal]``列出/去除``选项卡才会"
"显示。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:48
msgid ""
"In case the PTF should be removed using the API, the normal "
"[systemitem]``system.schedulePackageRemove`` api can be used with the proxy "
"package name."
msgstr ""
"如果应使用 API 去除 PTF，可以使用常规 [systemitem]``system."
"schedulePackageRemove`` API 和代理软件包名称。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Removing the patched version of a package on the client"
msgstr "在客户端上去除软件包的已修补版本"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:50
msgid ""
"In case a PTF should be removed directly on the client using the console, it "
"is required to use a special command [literal]``zypper removeptf``.  All "
"other ways result either in an error or can lead to unwanted behavior like "
"removing important packages from the system, and making the system unusable."
msgstr ""
"如果要使用控制台在客户端上直接去除 PTF，则需要使用特殊命令 [literal]``zypper "
"removeptf``。所有其他方法要么会产生错误，要么可能导致非预期行为，例如从系统中"
"去除重要软件包，致使系统不可用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/ptfs.adoc:51
msgid ""
"For the command line usage see also: https://www.suse.com/de-de/support/kb/"
"doc/?id=000020596"
msgstr ""
"另请参见 https://www.suse.com/de-de/support/kb/doc/?id=000020596 了解命令行用"
"法"

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Signing Repository Metadata"
msgstr "为储存库元数据签名"

#.  TODO: Explain why repository metadata should/would be signed.
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:2
msgid "You require a custom GPG key to be able to sign repository metadata."
msgstr "需有一个自定义 GPG 密钥才能为储存库元数据签名。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Generating a Custom GPG Key"
msgstr "过程：生成自定义 GPG 密钥"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:4
msgid ""
"As the root user, use the [command]``gpg`` command to generate a new key:"
msgstr "以 root 用户身份使用 [command]``gpg`` 命令生成新密钥："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "gpg --gen-key\n"
msgstr "gpg --gen-key\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:6
msgid ""
"At the prompts, select [systemitem]``RSA`` as the key type, with a size of "
"2048 bits, and select an appropriate expiry date for your key."
msgstr ""
"根据提示选择 [systemitem]``RSA`` 作为密钥类型，将大小指定为 2048 位，并为密钥"
"选择适当的失效日期。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:7
msgid ""
"Check the details for your new key, and type [systemitem]``y`` to confirm."
msgstr "检查新密钥的细节，然后键入 [systemitem]``y`` 以确认。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:8
msgid ""
"At the prompts, enter a name and email address to be associated with your "
"key."
msgstr "根据提示输入要与该密钥关联的名称和电子邮件地址。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:9
msgid ""
"You can also add a comment to help you identify the key, if desired.  When "
"you are happy with the user identity, type [systemitem]``O`` to confirm."
msgstr ""
"如果需要，您还可以添加注释以帮助识别该密钥。如果您对用户身份设置感到满意，请"
"键入 [systemitem]``O`` 以确认。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:10
msgid "At the prompt, enter a passphrase to protect your key."
msgstr "根据提示输入通行口令以保护您的密钥。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:11
msgid "The key should be automatically added to your keyring."
msgstr "该密钥应自动添加到您的密钥环。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:12
msgid "You can check by listing the keys in your keyring:"
msgstr "可以通过列出密钥环中的密钥进行检查："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "gpg --list-keys\n"
msgstr "gpg --list-keys\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Add the password for your keyring to the [filename]``/etc/rhn/signing.conf`` "
"configuration file, by opening the file in your text editor and adding this "
"line:"
msgstr ""
"在文本编辑器中打开 [filename]``/etc/rhn/signing.conf`` 配置文件并添加下面一行"
"内容，将密钥环的口令添加到该文件："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "GPGPASS=\"password\"\n"
msgstr "GPGPASS=\"password\"\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:16
msgid ""
"For renewing a GPG key, see xref:administration:troubleshooting/tshoot-sync."
"adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"有关如何续订 GPG 密钥，请参见 xref:administration:troubleshooting/tshoot-"
"sync.adoc[]。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:17
msgid ""
"You can manage metadata signing on the command line using the [command]``mgr-"
"sign-metadata-ctl`` command."
msgstr ""
"可以在命令行中使用 [command]``mgr-sign-metadata-ctl`` 命令来管理元数据签名。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Enabling Metadata Signing"
msgstr "过程：启用元数据签名"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:19
msgid "You need to know the short identifier for the key to use."
msgstr "您需要知道所要使用的密钥的短标识符。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:20
msgid "You can list your available public keys in short format:"
msgstr "可以简短格式列出可用的公共密钥："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"gpg --keyid-format short --list-keys\n"
"...\n"
"pub   rsa2048/3E7BFE0A 2019-04-02 [SC] [expires: 2021-04-01]\n"
"      A43F9EC645ED838ED3014B035CFA51BF3E7BFE0A\n"
"uid         [ultimate] SUSE Manager\n"
"sub   rsa2048/118DE7FF 2019-04-02 [E] [expires: 2021-04-01]\n"
msgstr ""
"gpg --keyid-format short --list-keys\n"
"...\n"
"pub   rsa2048/3E7BFE0A 2019-04-02 [SC] [expires: 2021-04-01]\n"
"      A43F9EC645ED838ED3014B035CFA51BF3E7BFE0A\n"
"uid         [ultimate] SUSE Manager\n"
"sub   rsa2048/118DE7FF 2019-04-02 [E] [expires: 2021-04-01]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:22
msgid ""
"Enable metadata signing with the [command]``mgr-sign-metadata-ctl`` command:"
msgstr "使用 [command]``mgr-sign-metadata-ctl`` 命令启用元数据签名："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mgr-sign-metadata-ctl enable 3E7BFE0A\n"
"OK. Found key 3E7BFE0A in keyring.\n"
"DONE. Set key 3E7BFE0A in /etc/rhn/signing.conf.\n"
"DONE. Enabled metadata signing in /etc/rhn/rhn.conf.\n"
"DONE. Exported key 4E2C3DD8 to /srv/susemanager/salt/gpg/mgr-keyring.gpg.\n"
"DONE. Exported key 4E2C3DD8 to /srv/www/htdocs/pub/mgr-gpg-pub.key.\n"
"NOTE. For the changes to become effective run:\n"
"   mgr-sign-metadata-ctl regen-metadata\n"
msgstr ""
"mgr-sign-metadata-ctl enable 3E7BFE0A\n"
"OK. Found key 3E7BFE0A in keyring.\n"
"DONE. Set key 3E7BFE0A in /etc/rhn/signing.conf.\n"
"DONE. Enabled metadata signing in /etc/rhn/rhn.conf.\n"
"DONE. Exported key 4E2C3DD8 to /srv/susemanager/salt/gpg/mgr-keyring.gpg.\n"
"DONE. Exported key 4E2C3DD8 to /srv/www/htdocs/pub/mgr-gpg-pub.key.\n"
"NOTE. For the changes to become effective run:\n"
"   mgr-sign-metadata-ctl regen-metadata\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:24
msgid "You can check that your configuration is correct with this command:"
msgstr "可以使用以下命令检查您的配置是否正确："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "mgr-sign-metadata-ctl check-config\n"
msgstr "mgr-sign-metadata-ctl check-config\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:26
msgid ""
"Restart the services and schedule metadata regeneration to pick up the "
"changes:"
msgstr "重启动服务并安排元数据重新生成以应用更改："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "mgr-sign-metadata-ctl regen-metadata\n"
msgstr "mgr-sign-metadata-ctl regen-metadata\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:28
msgid ""
"You can also use the [command]``mgr-sign-metadata-ctl`` command to perform "
"other tasks.  Use [command]``mgr-sign-metadata-ctl --help`` to see the "
"complete list."
msgstr ""
"还可以使用 [command]``mgr-sign-metadata-ctl`` 命令执行其他任务。使用 "
"[command]``mgr-sign-metadata-ctl --help`` 可查看完整列表。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:29
msgid ""
"Repository metadata signing is a global option.  When it is enabled, it is "
"enabled on all software channels on the server.  This means that all clients "
"connected to the server need to trust the new GPG key to be able to install "
"or update packages."
msgstr ""
"储存库元数据签名是全局选项。启用后，将对服务器上的所有软件通道启用该选项。这"
"意味着，连接到服务器的所有客户端需要信任新的 GPG 密钥才能安装或更新软件包。"

#. type: Block title
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Importing GPG keys on Clients"
msgstr "过程：在客户端上导入 GPG 密钥"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:31
msgid "Deploying GPG keys to the clients works with salt states."
msgstr "将 GPG 密钥部署到客户端的过程适用于 Salt 状态。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:32
msgid "Apply the highstate with the {productname} {webui}."
msgstr "使用 {productname} {webui} 应用 Highstate。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/repo-metadata.adoc:33
msgid ""
"For more information about troubleshooting GPG keys, see xref:administration:"
"troubleshooting/tshoot-sync.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"有关 GPG 密钥查错的详细信息，请参见 xref:administration:troubleshooting/"
"tshoot-sync.adoc[]。"

#. type: Title =
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Generate Reports"
msgstr "生成报告"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:2
msgid ""
"{productname} allows the user to produce a variety of reports.  These "
"reports can be helpful for taking inventory of your subscribed systems, "
"users, and organizations.  Using reports is often simpler than gathering "
"information manually from the {productname} {webui}, especially if you have "
"many systems under management."
msgstr ""
"{productname} 允许用户生成各种报告。这些报告有助于清点已订阅的系统、用户和组"
"织。使用报告通常比从 {productname} {webui} 手动收集信息更方便，尤其是要管理众"
"多的系统时。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:3
msgid ""
"While the command line tool [command]``spacewalk-report`` can be used to "
"generate pre-configured reports, with the introduction of the xref:"
"specialized-guides:large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc[Hub Reporting] it is "
"also possible to generate fully customized reports.  This can be achieved by "
"connecting any reporting tool that supports the SQL language to the "
"reporting database and extract the data directly.  For more information "
"about the data availability and structure, see the reporting database schema "
"documentation."
msgstr ""
"虽然可以使用命令行工具 [command]``spacewalk-report`` 生成预配置的报告，但随着"
"xref:specialized-guides:large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc[Hub Reporting]的"
"引入，也可以生成完全自定义的报告。可以通过将任何支持 SQL 语言的报告工具连接到"
"报告数据库并直接提取数据来实现此目的。有关数据可用性和结构的详细信息，请参见"
"报告数据库纲要文档。"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using ``spacewalk-report``"
msgstr "使用 ``spacewalk-report``"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:5
msgid ""
"To generate reports, you must have the [package]``spacewalk-reports`` "
"package installed.  The [command]``spacewalk-report`` command allows you to "
"organize and display reports about content, systems, and user resources "
"across {productname}."
msgstr ""
"要生成报告，必须安装 [package]``spacewalk-reports`` 软件包。使用 "
"[command]``spacewalk-report`` 命令可以组织和显示有关整个 {productname} 中的内"
"容、系统和用户资源的报告。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Due to the introduction of xref:specialized-guides:large-deployments/hub-"
"reporting.adoc[Hub Reporting], [command]``spacewalk-report`` now gathers by "
"default the data from the reporting database. See <<spacewalk-report-"
"reporting-db>> for more information."
msgstr ""
"由于xref:specialized-guides:large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc[Hub "
"Reporting]的引入，[command]``spacewalk-report`` 现在默认会从报告数据库中收集"
"数据。有关详细信息，请参见 <<spacewalk-report-reporting-db>>。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:7
msgid "You can generate reports on:"
msgstr "可以针对以下各项生成报告："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:8
msgid "System Inventory: list all the systems registered to {productname}."
msgstr "系统库存：列出所有已注册到 {productname} 的系统。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:9
msgid "Patches: list all the patches relevant to the registered systems."
msgstr "补丁：列出所有与已注册系统相关的补丁。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:10
msgid ""
"You can sort patches by severity, as well as the systems that apply to a "
"particular patch."
msgstr "可以按严重性以及适用于特定补丁的系统将补丁排序。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Users: list all registered users and any systems associated with a "
"particular user."
msgstr "用户：列出所有已注册用户以及与特定用户关联的所有系统。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:12
msgid ""
"To get the report in CSV format, run this command at the command prompt on "
"the server:"
msgstr "要获取 CSV 格式的报告，请在服务器上的命令提示符下运行以下命令："

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "spacewalk-report <report_name>\n"
msgstr "spacewalk-report <报告名称>\n"

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "``spacewalk-report`` and the reporting database"
msgstr "``spacewalk-report`` 和报告数据库"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:15
msgid ""
"[command]``spacewalk-report`` uses by default the new reporting database to "
"extract the data.  This means that the new generated reports will have some "
"differences in the structure and the format of the data.  The differences "
"common to all reports are:"
msgstr ""
"[command]``spacewalk-report`` 默认使用新的报告数据库来提取数据。这意味着，新"
"生成的报告在数据结构和格式方面存在一定的差异。所有报告的共同差异是："

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:16
msgid ""
"the report data is not changing in real-time, but it's updated only by the "
"execution of a scheduled task;"
msgstr "报告数据不会实时更改，而只能通过执行安排的任务来更新；"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:17
msgid ""
"data duplication has been removed and columns that were previously "
"considered \"multival\" contain now multiple values separated by ``;``. This "
"also means that the command line options ``--multival-on-rows`` and ``--"
"multival-separator`` are no longer applicable to the new reports, as their "
"behavior is now the default;"
msgstr ""
"已去除重复数据，以前被视为“多值”的列现在包含多个由 ``;`` 分隔的值。这也意味着"
"命令行选项 ``--multival-on-rows`` 和 ``--multival-separator`` 不再适用于新报"
"告，因为它们的行为现在是默认行为；"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:18
msgid ""
"in all reports the new columns ``mgm_id`` and ``synced_date`` have been "
"introduced to identify the management server in the hub scenario and the "
"last time the information was updated from the application database;"
msgstr ""
"在所有报告中引入了新列 ``mgm_id`` 和 ``synced_date``，以标识中心方案中的管理"
"服务器，以及上次从应用程序数据库更新信息的时间；"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:19
msgid ""
"all boolean values are now represented by the ``True``/``False`` and not by "
"a ``1``/``0`` values;"
msgstr ""
"现在，所有布尔值都由 ``True``/``False`` 表示，而不是由 ``1``/``0`` 值表示；"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:20
msgid ""
"the column ``org_id`` has been replaced by ``organization``, which contains "
"the organization name and not the numerical identifier;"
msgstr ""
"``org_id`` 列已由 ``organization`` 取代，后者包含组织名称而不是数字标识符；"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:21
msgid ""
"The term \"server\" has been replaced by \"system.\" So, for example, the "
"column ``server_id`` is now called ``system_id``."
msgstr ""
"“server”一词已由“system”取代。因此，举例而言，``server_id`` 列现在名为 "
"``system_id``。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:22
msgid "For report specific changes, see <<report-list>>."
msgstr "有关特定于报告的更改，请参见<<report-list>>。"

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:23
msgid ""
"If this changed behavior causes trouble, the new option ``--legacy-report`` "
"can be used to fall back to the old report, which is executed against the "
"application database."
msgstr ""
"如果这种行为更改造成了问题，可以使用新选项 ``--legacy-report`` 回退到针对应用"
"程序数据库执行的旧报告。"

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/administration/pages/reports.adoc:24
msgid ""
"For more information about hub reporting, see xref:specialized-guides:large-"
"deployments/hub-reporting.adoc[]."
msgstr ""
"有关中心报告的详细信息，请参见 xref:specialized-guides:large-deployments/hub-"
"reporting.adoc[]。"

